(47, 'SYSJ0170', 'Ahmed Saif Eldeen', 'ahmedsaifeldeen1314@gmail.com', '01091310012', 'Egypt', 'male', '2008-08-13', 'STEM', 'adsaf', '8', 'Linguistics', '5', 'Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. ', 'Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. ', 'Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. ', 5, '8-5', 'dsa', NULL, NULL, 'under_review', 'SYSJ0415', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-03 05:31:07', '{\"Linguistics\":\"5\"}', 1, NULL),
(48, 'SYSJ062', 'Abd El-Rahman Mousa', 'abdelrahmanmousa365@gmail.com', '+201015384128', 'Egypt', 'male', '2009-01-03', 'Scientific Creativity Center', 'G10', '3.73', 'Biology,Computer Science,Data Science,Environmental Science,Medicine & Public Health,Neuroscience & Neurobiology', 'N/A', 'You need more than just technical knowledge to be a good mentor in scientific research. You also need to be able to understand other people, be patient, and see their potential. This quote sums up what Ive learned about science from my own life.  Ive developed award-winning research projects, such as using Trichoderma to control Fusarium wilt biologically and making bioplastics from poultry feathers. Because of this, Ive learned a lot about concepts and also about the problems that young researchers face, like experiments that dont work, not knowing what to do, and being afraid of not being good enough.\r\nI have mentored peers on several scientific teams, including SCC and Researchers. On these teams, I often helped my teammates understand protocols, interpret results, and stay strong when things didnt go as planned.. I’ve found that helping others overcome these moments of doubt often matters more than the science itself — because it’s in those moments that curiosity is either broken or built.\r\nMy goal is to pursue biotechnology in higher education, with a long-term aim of guiding students in research that matters to communities. YSJ provides an ideal space for that not only because of its scientific rigor, but because it values mentorship as part of leadership.', 'Hey Team 123 \r\nI saw you havent submitted your Research Idea Proposal yet and wanted to follow up with you. The deadline has passed, it is very important to get your idea finalized so YSJ can act on the rest of the program.\r\nAs always, if you have any blockers or questions about anything at all, content, structure, direction, you can reach out. Just keep in mind that I need you to prioritize finishing and submitting your proposal as soon as possible, ideally in the next 24 hours.\r\nAs you know, YSJ is depending on the commitment of your team and I know you will deliver something great. Lets make it happen \r\nLooking forward to your idea\r\nAbd El-Rahman Mousa \r\nYSJ Senior Researcher', 'My research background comes from a deep curiosity about the application of research and science to our most pressing problems surrounding health, agriculture, and environmental issues in our communities. In the last six years, I have led and co-developed research projects that merge biology, sustainability, and innovation.\r\nMy early project was on tomato wilt disease with Trichoderma fungi as a biocontrol agent. Id a low-cost, environmentally friendly native to chemical pesticides. I tested the formulation in laboratory and greenhouse environments, which led to effective suppression of the growth of Fusarium. This project gained national recognition with a 2nd place award in microbiology at ISEF Egypt — but more important was my realization of the impact applied science could have on people’s lives.\r\nThis project also won Best Environmental Project at Climathon Egypt 2022 (sponsored by the EU), which also led to me being invited to speak as a youth representative at COP27.\r\n\r\nI then turned to plastic pollution by creating bioplastics from poultry feather waste, something very abundant and unused in Egypt. We produced a biodegradable plastic prototype through keratin extraction and natural crosslinking methods. \r\nI have also engaged in youth research communities such as SCC and Researchers, where I have had the opportunity to collaborate, mentor, and share experiences with my peers. Each opportunity has enhanced my technical skills but also deepened my belief that research can be used for meaningful impact, and I look forward to expanding my research trajectory with YSJ.', 10, '1-7:25-7 . 2-8:15-8 . 1-9:1-10 .', 'friend', NULL, NULL, 'approved', 'SYSJ0415', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-03 16:16:24', '{\"Biology\":\"7\",\"Computer Science\":\"6\",\"Data Science\":\"5\",\"Environmental Science\":\"8\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"7\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\"}', 0, 'Environmental Science & Bioinformatics'),
(49, 'SYSJ065', 'Basel Mahmoud', 'baselmsaa@gmail.com', '01140909700', 'Egypt', 'male', '2008-07-25', 'STEM High school for boys - 6th of October ', 'Rising senior (G12)', '4.0', 'Biology,Chemistry,Psychology', 'A in Biology, A in Chemistry.', 'As a member of YSJ season 2024, I have cultivated enough experience in research from this program to help students with their research. I have made a research paper on psychology and nutrition, where I attended all sessions and explored the junior notion dashboard clearly. I understand YSJ needs a patient senior who can motivate students to their limits for best research paper possible, and that is what I plan to do. I plan to intensively monitor them closely, preventing any possible procrastinations or mistakes. As a senior, the YSJ students are my top priority and I will be careful to guide them through the vast ocean of research. Because we are high school students, we are looked down upon as youth and we do not have many research opportunities because of this. That is why I plan to make to make this experience as delightful as possible for the juniors so they can maximize their available chances to the maximum. In other word, this is a once-in-a-life opportunity that I want to be a part of, to facilitate for young researchers. I will dedicate a portion of my time everyday to help and answer any questions they have. I know I am fit for this responsibility as I was a capstone assistant for 15 students on the span of 2 semesters. I helped them with their engineering projects, closely monitored them and reviewed their work to give them valuable feedback in a way that makes them always remember it. I responded to all their questions, performed many mock trials for them, and helped them achieve their best projects possible in architectural engineering and sustainable energy. Not only did I review their work, I also gave them sessions on how to academically write a research paper and how to write each section. Due to my outstanding performance, I have been picked to work on a Capstone Bootcamp to help many more students with their research expertise. I have been working in collaboration with other assistants on a comprehensive rubric to guide the students. Also, as a mentor in biology club magazine, I have guided many biology passionate students to write their first ever articles on a biology topic of their choice. I have reviewed their ideas, scientifically checked their information, and gave them feedback on their tasks. I also gave them sessions on academic writing and provided examples.', 'Hey team 123, Basel here. I have noticed you did not submit your research proposal on time. Are you facing any problems? You can always tell me, I will try my best to answer you. If you are facing any problems in real life like familial problems, you should also let me know. I know you are trying your best but sticking to deadlines is crucial for your scientific integrity and later on in life. If there is something you are embarrassed to discuss with your teammate, you can dm me. I hope to get a reply from you soon. @member1 @member2', 'I have immersed myself in various fields, either STEM or Non-STEM. As a member of YSJ season 2024, I have worked in collaboration with another student on Psychology and nutrition. The paper explored the relation between nutrition problems and mental illness ADHD in boarding school students. This research incorporated a survey, comprehensive literature review, and conclusive results. I had a perfect attendance and got a 88 on the final rating. I also participated with the paper in IFYR and achieved outstanding performance in the second round. As a STEM student, I have to do a research project each semester as a part of our curriculum. My proudest project is the one I made in environmental/chemical engineering to help with air purification. It is a proposed solution with a prototype utilizing an automated system with KOH to decrease CO2 concentration in the air. I performed this project alongside 3 of my peers, which helped me achieve the 1st place out of 2000+ students in STEM. I will attach the portfolio for the project below. STEM curriculum being dependent on self-learning and open sources have made me a natural at research for knowledge I need. I made plenty of presentations and projects for the teachers, such as a biology project about generating sustainable energy incorporating biology. As a student in STEM, I engaged in extracurriculars such as being a member in biology club, later becoming a magazine mentor making presentations and explaining sessions about research and article crafting.', 8, 'Nothing so far but i will give a notice before', 'through my school, i was a member last season.', NULL, NULL, 'under_review', 'SYSJ0415', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-03 17:56:39', '{\"Biology\":\"7\",\"Chemistry\":\"5\",\"Psychology\":\"8\"}', 1, NULL),
(50, 'SYSJ0182', 'Ali Kotb', 'ali.2523056@stemelsadat.moe.edu.eg', '01097444712', 'Egypt', 'male', '2007-03-03', 'STEM El Sadat School', 'G12', '4/4', 'Computer Science,Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering),Mathematics,Robotics', 'Computer Science: A - Engineering: N/A', 'To truly explain a concept is not merely to know it it is to understand it so deeply that you can make it clear to others.  During my whole life, especially after Joining STEM schools, This relation was always kept consistent while avoiding any flaw in it, Beginning from my first capstone project, I found a mentor which was at G11 at that time mentoring me during my research project especially for the portfolio, He passed a lot of knowledge for me making me able to achieve A+ in the project, even when I became at G11, I helped a team that I found that they didn’t know a lot of basics in the capstone project, like the poster and its sections, I arranged a one-hour weekly session for them explaining everything they need, whether in the poster, portfolio, or even the prototype, Helping 2 of them achieve A+.\r\nAnd it was never just in STEM. During my ISEF project, beside the research skills I gained from the school, I asked an ISEF Finalist student to assist me during my process, which helped me reach the final stage in Egypt to be a national finalist. Recently, I got to Pioneer Academics Research Program SU25 in CS with my professor, David Perkins. In our first group sessions, I found that he is not only prepared, but he has also thought about what challenges we might face and how to deal with them. This is what is called real mentoring, you are not just giving knowledge, you really help in dealing with a specific topic.\r\nIn YSJ, I hope not just to be a mentor, but I hope to be a friend where juniors find me a solution while they face challenges. Not just afraid of asking, listen for their challenges, make them feel that I faced what they faced, which will really help them deal with me without feeling worried. My goal is not just to be a mentor and assist them in doing research, I want to make it like a journey where they love listening to and also love the journey they are in, which will lead to a better understanding, to make them do their best.\r\n\r\nTo learn more about me, please check my Online portfolio on: https://alimohamed.me/\r\n', 'Hi Team 123 ,\r\n\r\nI trust your week is going well!. Thanks again for the discussions and brainstorming sessions so far—your energy has been noticed \r\n\r\nThat said, I noticed your Research Idea Proposal hasn’t been submitted yet. This is a key step in the research cycle, and falling behind here could limit the impact and clarity of your future work. If you believe you’ve already submitted it, please let me know right away so I can double-check on my end.\r\n\r\nThis proposal is designed to help you clarify your direction and receive valuable feedback early—delays reduce the usefulness of that process. We’re offering a short extension: please submit it no later than Tuesday, July 2nd\r\nLet me know if you’re running into any blockers or need input from me before then. You’ve got this \r\nYSJ Senior Researcher', 'Recently, I got into Pioneer academics computer science field with Professor David Perkins discussing Community Detection and NP-Hard Problems, using the Julia Programming language, discussing problems that are easy to identify but hard to solve.\r\nThis will help me not just benefit from it, but it will also help me ask him for additional help in research if needed, while being a senior researcher in YSJ.\r\nbeside the Capstone project, I’ve worked on a lot of research. The first was for my ISEF project. I’ve used LaTeX to write it, and because it was really good, the evaluator asked me if I had published it yet. I’ve also worked on my research paper titled: Neural Interfaces and Cybersecurity Safeguarding Brain-Integrated Technologies, in this research I was discussing For about 3 Months, I was getting into how the chips decode signals from the brain when performing a function on a device and transmit these signals again to your brain. In addition to discussing how this chip might be hacked and its Impacts. My passion for cybersecurity compels me to examine Neuralink from a detective’s perspective, evaluating its security and safety risks. \r\nI’m working on the publication process, but as I learnt from Pioneer, it is not so essential, especially when you are in high school, which I see it is something exceptional that YSJ offers. Currently, I have a ResearchGate account, you can see it on: https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Ali-Kotb-5/research\r\n\r\nLink for Silentra Research as it is more than 10 Mb: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dFKleLgx2eExL1ariYlF08pHjV-7zSYE/view?usp=sharing\r\n', 8, 'Between the start of June and the end of September, I am primarily engaged with the Pioneer Academics program, which runs until mid-August. During this period, I am generally available from Tuesday to Thursday. However, I believe I can also manage YSJ responsibilities on the other days of the week with proper planning.  Additionally, at the beginning of August, I will be slightly less available as I will be preparing for the SAT exam scheduled for that month. That said, as a senior researcher, I am confident in my ability to manage these commitments effectively.', 'My Brother was a senior researcher at YSJ', NULL, NULL, 'approved', 'SYSJ0416', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-06 06:05:04', '{\"Computer Science\":\"10\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"5\",\"Mathematics\":\"5\",\"Robotics\":\"8\"}', 0, 'Computer Science & Engineering'),
(51, 'SYSJ0360', 'Basel Mahmoud', 'baselmsaa@gmail.com', '01140909700', 'Egypt', 'male', '2008-07-25', 'STEM High school for boys - 6th of October', 'G12 (Rising senior)', '4.0', 'Biology,Chemistry,Psychology', 'A in Biology, A in Chemistry for G11, B+ in biology and B+ in chemistry for G10.', 'As a member of YSJ season 2024, I have cultivated enough experience in research from this program to help students with their research. I have made a research paper on psychology and nutrition, where I attended all sessions and explored the junior notion dashboard clearly. I understand YSJ needs a patient senior who can motivate students to their limits for best research paper possible, and that is what I plan to do. I plan to intensively monitor them closely, preventing any possible procrastinations or mistakes. As a senior, the YSJ students are my top priority and I will be careful to guide them through the vast ocean of research. Because we are high school students, we are looked down upon as youth and we do not have many research opportunities because of this. That is why I plan to make to make this experience as delightful as possible for the juniors so they can maximize their available chances to the maximum. In other word, this is a once-in-a-life opportunity that I want to be a part of, to facilitate for young researchers. I will dedicate a portion of my time everyday to help and answer any questions they have. I know I am fit for this responsibility as I was a capstone assistant for 15 students on the span of 2 semesters. I helped them with their engineering projects, closely monitored them and reviewed their work to give them valuable feedback in a way that makes them always remember it. I responded to all their questions, performed many mock trials for them, and helped them achieve their best projects possible in architectural engineering and sustainable energy. Not only did I review their work, I also gave them sessions on how to academically write a research paper and how to write each section. Due to my outstanding performance, I have been picked to work on a Capstone Bootcamp to help many more students with their research expertise. I have been working in collaboration with other assistants on a comprehensive rubric to guide the students. Also, as a mentor in biology club magazine, I have guided many biology passionate students to write their first ever articles on a biology topic of their choice. I have reviewed their ideas, scientifically checked their information, and gave them feedback on their tasks. I also gave them sessions on academic writing and provided examples.', 'Hey team 123, Basel here. I have noticed you did not submit your research proposal on time. Are you facing any problems? You can always tell me, I will try my best to answer you. I know you are trying your best but sticking to deadlines is crucial for your scientific integrity and later on in life.  Also, failing to adhere by deadlines can deduct points from your final paper rating. If there is something you are embarrassed to discuss with your teammate, you can dm me. I hope to get a reply from you soon. @member1 @member2', 'I have immersed myself in various fields, either STEM or Non-STEM. As a member of YSJ season 2024, I have worked in collaboration with another student on Psychology and nutrition. The paper explored the relation between nutrition problems and mental illness ADHD in boarding school students. This research incorporated a survey, comprehensive literature review, and conclusive results. I had a perfect attendance and got a 88 on the final rating. I also participated with the paper in IFYR and achieved outstanding performance in the second round. As a STEM student, I have to do a research project each semester as a part of our curriculum. My proudest project is the one I made in environmental/chemical engineering to help with air purification. It is a proposed solution with a prototype utilizing an automated system with KOH to decrease CO2 concentration in the air. I performed this project alongside 3 of my peers, which helped me achieve the 1st place out of 2000+ students in STEM. I will attach the portfolio for the project below. STEM curriculum being dependent on self-learning and open sources have made me a natural at research for knowledge I need. I made plenty of presentations and projects for the teachers, such as a biology project about generating sustainable energy incorporating biology. As a student in STEM, I engaged in extracurriculars such as being a member in biology club, later becoming a magazine mentor making presentations and explaining sessions about research and article crafting.', 8, 'Nothing for now, but I will notify before.', 'from my school, I was a member.', NULL, NULL, 'approved', 'SYSJ052', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-05 20:31:20', '{\"Biology\":\"7\",\"Chemistry\":\"5\",\"Psychology\":\"8\"}', 0, 'Psycology'),
(52, 'SYSJ0113', 'Ahmed H.Ali', 'ahmedhazemcoding@gmail.com', '+20 101 605 6140', 'Egyptian', 'male', '2007-01-01', 'Applied Technology School for Nuclear Energy in El-Dabaa', 'G12', '4.0', 'Computer Science,Robotics', 'G10: 3.9, G11: 4.0, G12: 4.0', 'Mentorship in scientific research requires more than just technical knowledge—it demands the ability to empathize with learners, break down complex ideas, and nurture intellectual curiosity. My experiences in developing a self-supervised monocular 3D perception framework have immersed me in both rigorous theoretical work and iterative problem-solving, preparing me to meet the high standards of the Young Scientist Journal (YSJ).\r\n\r\nAcademically, I aim to make advanced concepts in computer vision, optimization, and sensor fusion accessible to early researchers. My goal as a mentor is to help students see research not as a daunting challenge but as an exciting journey of discovery. At YSJ, the emphasis on student-led exploration and publication is aligned with my philosophy of enabling young minds to take ownership of their work.\r\n\r\nThroughout my project, I have often taken the role of a guide—whether helping peers debug pose graph optimizers, explaining photometric loss functions to beginners, or walking a teammate through stereo-based triangulation using camera poses. In one particular situation, a fellow student struggled to understand how IMU drift affects visual odometry. I d visual demos using matplotlib to illustrate the concept and guided them through fusing IMU and GPS using Kalman filtering, which deepened their understanding and sparked their interest in sensor fusion research.\r\n\r\nYSJ provides a unique platform where scientific rigor meets youth-driven passion. I believe I can use this environment to help aspiring researchers channel their questions into well-structured projects, guiding them from ideation to presentation, just as I navigated the challenges of building a scalable 3D perception system with limited resources. I’m excited to share not only the technical tools, but also the mindset and confidence necessary to thrive in research.', 'Hey Team 123,\r\nJust a reminder that your Research Idea Proposal is past due. We haven’t seen a submission yet, and I wanted to check in and make sure everything’s okay on your end.\r\n\r\nThis is a key step to get feedback early and keep your project on track—plus, missing deadlines can delay your review process later on. If you’re stuck or need input before submitting, I’m here to help.\r\n\r\nPlease prioritize wrapping this up and share it with me by [ date/time]. Let me know if you’re facing blockers.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n[Your Name]\r\nYSJ Senior Researcher', 'My research background lies at the intersection of computer vision, sensor fusion, and autonomous systems. I am a Pioneer Academics alumnus in Computer Vision, where I conducted supervised research on image-based 3D reconstruction, focusing on spatial transformations and photometric loss, culminating in a university-level research paper and academic presentation.\r\n\r\nMost recently, I developed and led a project titled “Self-Supervised Metric-Scaled Monocular 3D Perception Framework for Low-Cost Autonomous Systems,” which was awarded Grand Award at BASEF (Bibliotheca Alexandrina Science and Engineering Fair). As a result, I proudly represented Egypt at Regeneron ISEF 2025 in Ohio, USA. My project focused on using monocular cameras alongside IMU, GPS, and barometer data to generate metric-scaled 3D maps without requiring expensive LiDAR or labeled datasets. The system integrated visual-inertial odometry, self-supervised depth estimation, and pose graph optimization, and was built to run in real-time on embedded hardware like the Raspberry Pi.\r\n\r\nMy research has been formally presented through ISEF-approved abstracts and project presentations, and I’ve worked extensively with tools such as PyTorch, OpenCV, and Ceres Solver for nonlinear optimization. Beyond technical implementation, I actively mentor and support peers in breaking down complex robotics and perception concepts.\r\n\r\nThese experiences have not only deepened my expertise in autonomous vision systems but also strengthened my commitment to empowering others in the research community.', 9, 'N/A', 'Friend of mine, he suggested to participate in IYFR and achived the first place.', NULL, NULL, 'approved', 'SYSJ0415', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2025-07-03 19:25:54', '{\"Computer Science\":\"10\",\"Robotics\":\"10\"}', 0, 'Robotics'),
(53, 'SYSJ0367', 'Ahmed Saif Eldeen', 'ahmedsaifeldeen1314@gmail.com', '+201091310012', 'Egypt', 'male', '2008-08-13', 'STEM', 'GRade 11', '4.0', 'Aerospace Engineering', 'B+', 'Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science. Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science.Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\r\n\r\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\r\n\r\nFurthermore