('SYSJ0146', '{\"full-name\":\"Mostafa mohamed \",\"email-address\":\"01060515631sasa@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01022440274\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-10-01\",\"institution\":\"No\",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"4\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Aerospace Engineering\":\"6\",\"Computer Science\":\"7\",\"Education\":\"8\",\"Environmental Science\":\"6\",\"Mathematics\":\"8\",\"Robotics\":\"9\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours\":\"\",\"time-blocks\":\"\",\"hear\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 18:52:28'),
('SYSJ0147', '{\"full-name\":\"aya abdelaty mohamed\",\"email-address\":\"ayaabdelaty2008@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01272587074\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-03-02\",\"institution\":\"Menofia STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"3.78\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"B+ TOTAL\",\"first-essay\":\"C\",\"second-essay\":\"C\",\"third-essay\":\"d\",\"hours\":\"4\",\"time-blocks\":\"Every Thursday and Friday from 6:00 pm to 10:00 pm \",\"hear\":\"from LinkedIn \"}', '[]', '2025-06-21 03:30:07'),
('SYSJ0148', '{\"full-name\":\"Arja Saxena\",\"email-address\":\"arja.sax@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+971 502164416\",\"country\":\"India\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-11-09\",\"institution\":\"GEMS Founders\",\"grade-year\":\"Year 12 \",\"gpa\":\"(GPA is unapplicable in British Schools, however I have majorities of As and A*s)\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Chemistry,Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering),Medicine & Public Health\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"9\",\"Chemistry\":\"7\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"6\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Bio- A* [GCSES], Chem-A\",\"first-essay\":\"When tutoring, I simplify tough science topics by using mnemonics and relatable analogies. For example, to explain enzyme activity affected by temperature and pH, I compared enzymes to \\u201cmachines\\u201d that work best under certain conditions. This helped students understand and remember the concept more easily. \\r\\nIn another case, I guided students through difficult genetic cross problems by introducing step-by-step logic and easy-to-remember phrases, which made the problems less intimidating. My approach focuses not just on getting the right answers, but also on fostering curiosity, encouraging students to ask  \\u201cwhy\\u201d and explore further. I\\u2019ve found that this method shifts their mindset from feeling overwhelmed to feeling excited about science.\\r\\nSeeing learners grow from confusion to genuine interest is the most rewarding part. It reminds me that science is not just about memorising facts but about understanding patterns and processes, and that effective communication can turn frustration into motivation.\",\"second-essay\":\"Hey Team 123! Just a heads-up that the Research Idea Proposal deadline has passed. No stress \\u2014 if you\\u2019re struggling or need help, feel free to reach out to me anytime. I\\u2019m here to support you, not to freak out! Let\\u2019s get this wrapped up soon so we can keep things moving. You got this!\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours\":\"\",\"time-blocks\":\"\",\"hear\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-21 08:41:52'),
('SYSJ0149', '{\"full-name\":\"Primos Khatiwoda\",\"email-address\":\"primoskhatiwada@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"9813749491\",\"country\":\"Nepal\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2011-09-26\",\"institution\":\"Kankai Secondary School\",\"grade-year\":\"9\",\"gpa\":\"3.98\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"A+\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in science is like guiding someone through a jungle of formulas with only a flashlight of curiosity and a backpack full of snacks (which is really just metaphors and coffee). I\\u2019ve learned that understanding scientific concepts is not just about memorizing equations, but about seeing the invisible thread that connects a question to a possibility. As Carl Sagan once said, \\u201cSomewhere, something incredible is waiting to be known.\\u201d My goal is to help young researchers believe they can find it.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy own research journey, filled with black holes, quantum weirdness, philosophy, and the occasional existential crisis, has taught me how confusing things sound like poetry. Just like a good poem is full of feeling and meaning, I want my research papers to have that same kind of heart and beauty. Which doesn\\u2019t come just from logic, but from passion and the wonder behind every discovery.\\r\\n\\r\\nAt YSJ, I see a place where high standards meet high hopes. It\\u2019s a platform that doesn\\u2019t just showcase young voices, but sharpens them. My mentoring goal is to make sure every student I work with feels not just smarter, but braver. Braver to ask wild questions, test mad ideas, and even fail gloriously, because that\\u2019s how real science happens.\\r\\n\\r\\nI remember helping a younger student once who thought time travel was nonsense. After two hours of talking about wormholes, paradoxes, and why Doctor Strange is a surprisingly decent physicist, they left the conversation wanting to write their own theory. It wasn\\u2019t just teaching them\\u2014it was watching them begin to see wonder in the chaos. My last words were, \\u201cWe don\\u2019t read, write, or research astrophysics because it\\u2019s cute. We do it because we are members of the human race, and the human race is filled with passion. Law, business, medicine, engineering\\u2014these are noble pursuits necessary to sustain life. But astrophysics, poetry, research\\u2014these are the things we live for.\\u201d \\r\\n\\r\\nWhile making students believe in themselves, what I truly offer is a voice that believes every learner has something beautiful to discover. And with YSJ\\u2019s resources, reach, and brilliance, I know I can help light that path a little further.\",\"second-essay\":\"Hey Team 123!\\r\\n\\r\\nFirst off, I want to say I really appreciate the effort and creativity you\\u2019ve shown so far. Your ideas have so much potential, and it\\u2019s exciting to see where this project could go.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you\\u2019re stuck or feeling overwhelmed, just say the word. We\\u2019re all here to figure this out together. Remember, great ideas take time, but finishing them on time takes teamwork and a little push.\\r\\n\\r\\nYou\\u2019ve got this, and I\\u2019m excited to see what you come up with! Let\\u2019s make it happen.\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours\":\"\",\"time-blocks\":\"\",\"hear\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-21 09:46:45'),
('SYSJ0150', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours\":\"\",\"time-blocks\":\"\",\"hear\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-21 09:51:13'),
('SYSJ0151', '{\"full-name\":\"Youssef Ayman Shafiq\",\"email-address\":\"yousefayman.14.11.2007@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201204559862\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-11-14\",\"institution\":\"Scholars secondary school in Ain Shams \",\"grade-year\":\"Second secondary \",\"gpa\":\"96%\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"98%\",\"first-essay\":\"In scientific research, mentoring calls for more than just a thorough comprehension of ideas it also calls for empathy, clarity, and the capacity to patiently and supportively lead young minds through difficulties. As an Egyptian high school student who is passionate about biology and the medical sciences, I have honed my understanding of scientific methodology as well as my capacity to explain difficult concepts and assist colleagues with their research projects. I want to study medicine or the life sciences because I think science should be applied to help people and pique peoples interest. My idea of mentorship as a collaborative, motivating experience is perfectly aligned with YSJs distinctive environment, which blends academic rigor with student-centered support.\\r\\nI have assisted younger students in developing precise hypotheses and conducting data analysis during scientific workshops and school exhibits. For instance, one group had trouble coming up with a good experiment however, with the help of step-by-step mentoring and guided questioning, they were able to produce a strong project and win a local science competition. I learned from that experience that fostering excitement and confidence rather than providing answers is the key to effective mentoring. As a student and young researcher, joining YSJ would mark a sea change in my career, and I would be honored to uphold its standards with zeal and dedication.\",\"second-essay\":\"To Team 123, I hope you are doing well. Im contacting you because I saw that you havent yet submitted your research idea proposal. Missing this crucial phase in the YSJ research timeline could hinder your progress and reduce the amount of time you have for revisions and feedback. Please dont hesitate to get in touch with me if youre having any trouble coming up with the idea, planning the proposal, or cooperating with others. Im here to help and support you during this process.\\r\\nPlease try to submit your proposal in the next 24 to 48 hours. Its better to have something we can work on together than to wait for a \\\"perfect\\\" version, even if your draft isn\'t flawless. I\'m eager to hear your thoughts! Warm regards, Senior Researcher, YSJ Program, Youssef Ayman Shafiq\",\"third-essay\":\"My strong interest in biology and the medical sciences, which I developed during my time in high school, is the foundation of my research background. Ive seized every chance to participate in science outside of the classroom because Im an enthusiastic learner. I have taken part in a number of national workshops and school-based science fairs that have focused on genetics, experimental biology, and public health awareness. Creating and carrying out a group biology project on the impact of various plant extracts on bacterial growth was one of my most fulfilling experiences. I oversaw the phases of data collection, analysis, and experimental setup. Because of its scientific rigor and relevance to antibiotic resistance, a topic I am extremely passionate about, our project was chosen to be presented at a regional science exhibition.\\r\\nI have mentored younger students during biology club activities and project-based learning sessions in addition to conducting research. In addition to boosting their confidence, I also deepened my own comprehension of scientific leadership and communication by assisting them in formulating precise hypotheses, organizing their research, and interpreting the findings. Even though I havent received any official publications or patents yet, I still view my research as being in its early but promising stages. Through initiatives like YSJ, Im determined to build on this foundation in order to make a significant contribution and develop as a young researcher.\",\"hours\":\"15\",\"time-blocks\":\"All days \",\"hear\":\"Friend \"}', '[]', '2025-06-21 13:58:22'),
('SYSJ0152', '{\"full-name\":\"Nazym Kairat\",\"email-address\":\"kairatnazym2007@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+77758100120\",\"country\":\"Kazakhstan\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-05-28\",\"institution\":\"Nazarbayev Intellectual School of Chemistry and Biology in Almaty\",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"4.9\\/5.0\",\"interest\":[\"Economics,Philosophy,Psychology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Economics\":\"8\",\"Philosophy\":\"9\",\"Psychology\":\"7\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Not applicable\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours\":\"\",\"time-blocks\":\"\",\"hear\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-21 14:17:47'),
