('SYSJ0183', '{\"full-name\":\"Salma Mohamed \",\"email-address\":\"salmaafalla21@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201286733313\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-01-21\",\"institution\":\"Abu bakr Elseddiq high school \",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"3.85\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Education,Environmental Science,History & Civilizations,Mathematics,Medicine & Public Health,Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"9\",\"Education\":\"5\",\"Environmental Science\":\"4\",\"History & Civilizations\":\"8\",\"Mathematics\":\"8\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"5\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"6\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Biology 97%\\/Maths 98%\\/History 99%\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-22 18:43:25'),
('SYSJ0184', '{\"full-name\":\"Ganat Ahmed ElSharkawy \",\"email-address\":\"ganatelsharkawi@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01554757836\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-06-07\",\"institution\":\"Future language school \",\"grade-year\":\"Grade 10\",\"gpa\":\"4\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-04 02:32:16'),
('SYSJ0185', '{\"full-name\":\"Hana Sameh \",\"email-address\":\"hanasameh2505@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01100225206\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-01-23\",\"institution\":\"Red Sea STEM school\",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"3.7\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"Biololgy B+, Chemisty B+\",\"first-essay\":\"This quote resonates deeply with my philosophy toward both learning and teaching in the sciences. Effective mentorship is not only about expertise in a subject but about creating an environment where curiosity thrives, and challenges are embraced as learning opportunity.\\r\\nThroughout my academic journey in STEM, I have actively engaged in both conducting research and supporting the young students in their journey. Leading teams like the counseling team and managing the coaching committee in TEDx STEM fayoum taught me the importance of empathy, and fostering a problem-solving mindset.\\r\\nI have been involved in developing prototypes like Electro-Step, a device generating electricity from footstep, and Early-Seizure detection. I have participated in competitions with these projects like UGRF, and my project have qualified in ISEF competition from 70 projects in my school to the Administration. I encountered technical and theoretical challenges, from optimizing electromagnetic induction to produce electricity from walking and I reached to this solution by searching on how to produce electricity from walking. I gained also skills about how to search, as first I only knew what is seizure but making research I reached to an effective solution of how to detect this disease early and decrease the injury. These experiences refined my ability to break down complex problems, identify patterns, and collaborate with teammates who came from different academic backgrounds.\\r\\nMy academic goal is to pursue medical with discovering treatments by focusing my career on researching about the diseases, while my mentoring goal is to guide young researchers through the exciting world of scientific inquiry. I aim to help them realize that uncertainty is a natural part of research and that even unexpected result has the potential to lead to meaningful discoveries.\\r\\nOne particularly memorable example was when a student at our school struggled with an Arduino project to measure pH for environmental science exhibition. They were overwhelmed by sensor calibration and coding issues. I sat with them over several afternoons, explaining communication skills, debugging their code line by line, and helping them grasp the importance of data validation. Their confidence grew, and they successfully presented their project well at the school fair.\",\"second-essay\":\"Hey Team 123, \\r\\nI hope you are doing well. I wanted to check in because I noticed we have missed the submission deadline for your Research Idea Proposal. I understand things can get busy, and research isnt always a smooth process but You can do it.\\r\\nThis proposal is your chance to set a clear direction and get valuable feedback before diving deeper, so its really important we get it in as soon as possible. please prioritize finalizing it and submitting by ( set new clear deadline).\\r\\nIf you are facing specific challenges, or stuck at any point, reach out here.\\r\\nHana,\\r\\nYSJ Senior Researcher\",\"third-essay\":\"My research background is rooted in multidisciplinary STEM fields, with a particular focus on medical concepts. As a high school student in a STEM school, I have engaged in several independent and team-based projects addressing real-world problems through innovative, research-based solution.\\r\\nOne of my notable projects was Early-Seizure detection, a cap designed to detect the seizure early to prevent the injury and the bad effects. I led a team with my colleague through the research process from hypothesis formulation and prototyping to field testing and data analysis. This project was presented at ISEF competition and we qualified to the second stage with taking the 20th place form 70 projects. \\r\\nAdditionally, I have worked on Electro-Step\\\", a stair designed to generate electricity from footsteps using electromagnetic induction. We tested our prototype in high-football areas such as school queues, measuring voltage output under varying conditions.\\r\\nI also contribute to science communication and mentoring. As vice head of the counseling team in my school, I have guided peers through the admission process, and fostering a culture of collaborative inquiry.\\r\\nThese experiences have prepared me to both conduct meaningful research and mentor others in the process. I aim to pursue further research in medicine and medical diagnostics innovation, specifically developing accessible healthcare technologies for underserved communities. I believe platforms like YSJ would amplify these efforts, allowing me to contribute to and learn from an international community of young researchers.\",\"hours_commitment\":\"8\",\"time_blocks\":\"August, september\",\"hear\":\"my fiend\"}', '[]', '2025-06-22 21:59:06'),
