('SYSJ0209', '{\"full-name\":\"Abd Elrahman Selim\",\"email-address\":\"selimabdelrahman989@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201029523678\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-03-12\",\"institution\":\"Dakahlia STEM High School\",\"grade-year\":\"G11\",\"gpa\":\"3.98\",\"interest\":\"Physics & Astrophysics\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Physics G10: A+, Physics G11: A\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"Hello, my best team! I heard a quote for Alice Walker that says: The most common way people give up their power is by thinking they do not have any.  I know you are busy and coming up with a new idea is quite hard, but I trust in you. You failed to stick to the deadline, but you will never fail to meet my expectations and push your boundaries in research. Research is not just a task or an assignment, it is the way in which you benefit the humanity and safe people s lives. Stay motivated and work hard! I am looking forward to receiving the task at the weekend!  \",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-24 18:37:05'),
('SYSJ0210', '{\"full-name\":\"Sama Elsayed Saber Awad \",\"email-address\":\"hdjsgdjeizj663737722@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01020998216\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-02-02\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":\"\",\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-24 18:26:11'),
('SYSJ0211', '{\"full-name\":\"Hydy Hussein \",\"email-address\":\"hydyhussein05@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201104532241\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-02-16\",\"institution\":\"Not Available \",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":\"\",\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-24 19:06:06'),
('SYSJ0213', '{\"full-name\":\"Menna Khalifa \",\"email-address\":\"mennakhalifa670@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201068011626\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2010-03-30\",\"institution\":\"Kotama secondary school \",\"grade-year\":\"G10\",\"gpa\":\"4.0\",\"interest\":\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy,Gender Studies & Inequality,International Relations & Government\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"6\",\"Gender Studies & Inequality\":\"7\",\"International Relations & Government\":\"7\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-24 20:46:21'),
('SYSJ0214', '{\"full-name\":\"Razan Mohamed \",\"email-address\":\"razanmohamed4341@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201033587187\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-06-23\",\"institution\":\"STEM 11TH DISTRICT high school \",\"grade-year\":\"10\",\"gpa\":\"4\\/4\",\"interest\":\"Biology,Neuroscience & Neurobiology\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"10\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"4\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Biology: A, Neuroscience: I have not take it to school before\",\"first-essay\":\"A true mentor is someone who understands the science deeply, yet knows how to guide others patiently through the learning process. This quote resonates with me because it reflects what I\\u2019ve experienced both as a researcher and as a leader in school biology activities. My work in scientific research\\u2014especially in biology and neuroscience\\u2014has taught me how to think critically and creatively, while also helping others do the same.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy research background encompasses conducting research on topics related to cancer treatment and cognitive science, and each experience has given me an even deeper sense of appreciation for how science can make lives better. Still more importantly, these experiences taught me just how steep the learning curve is. That\\u2019s why I\\u2019ve committed myself to mentoring\\u2014whether it was supporting students in the biology club, helping explain complex topics during team projects, or encouraging others to push past frustration and rediscover their love for science.\\r\\n\\r\\nYSJs values of excellence, teamwork, and student-centered inquiry are the very same I also hope to attain. I want to cultivate myself as a researcher while helping others become confident speakers of science. To be part of an environment that acknowledges curiosity and mentoring would allow me to help other young scientists not just to understand concepts, but to find direction and meaning in what they do.\\r\\n\\r\\nIhave seen the power of a single conversation in changing the attitude of a student toward science. From helping club members plan their first experiments to leading teammates through challenging moments in our projects, I have  learned that mentorship is just as important as research. At YSJ, I hope to further blend both\\u2014to learn, to mentor, and to grow with the next generation of ambitious thinkers.\\r\\n\",\"second-essay\":\"Hello Team 123,\\r\\n\\r\\nIve noticed that your Research Idea Proposal hasnt been submitted yet, even though the deadline passed. I understand that things get backed up sometimes, but its very important to keep to timings when youre doing research, and more so when youre in a team.\\r\\n\\r\\nAt this point, it is crucial that you finish and send your proposal in the next 24 hours. Should you be facing some issues, dont hesitate to let me know and we will sort them together. I am here to help, but I need you to meet me half-way.\\r\\n\\r\\nLooking forward to your .\\r\\n\\r\\nBest,\\r\\nRazan Mohamed\\r\\n\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-24 21:27:43');
INSERT INTO `application_drafts` (`user_id`, `data`, `files`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('SYSJ0215', '{\"full-name\":\"Judy Mahmoud \",\"email-address\":\"judymahmoud6200@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201203537560\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-06-17\",\"institution\":\"KAFR EL SHIEKH STEM school \",\"grade-year\":\"G11\",\"gpa\":\"3.134\",\"interest\":[\"Computer Science,Economics,Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering),Environmental Science,International Relations & Government,Mathematics,Physics & Astrophysics,Robotics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Computer Science\":\"5\",\"Economics\":\"5\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"5\",\"Environmental Science\":\"5\",\"International Relations & Government\":\"5\",\"Mathematics\":\"5\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"5\",\"Robotics\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Non\",\"first-essay\":\"Scientific mentorship requires more than academic knowledge it demands a genuine passion for conveying understanding, and the ability to motivate and guide students throughout their research journey. From my personal experience, I\\u2019ve learned that a strong knowledge base is essential, but not sufficient on its own. It must be paired with emotional intelligence, continuous encouragement, and the ability to  a safe intellectual environment that fosters curiosity and discovery.\\r\\n\\r\\nThroughout my academic path, I have always strived to enhance my ability to simplify complex scientific concepts and transform them into engaging, interactive learning experiences. I\\u2019ve collaborated with peers and younger learners in small research projects, where we encountered both conceptual and technical challenges. In one instance, during a school science club activity, some students struggled to understand the mechanism of a physics experiment. I developed a visual model to help them grasp the idea more intuitively, which sparked their enthusiasm and deepened their interest in the topic.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy academic goals are to specialize in applied physics while continuing to develop my educational and mentoring skills. I believe science is only complete when shared, and I am confident in my ability to contribute to YSJ\\u2019s mission of guiding young researchers in alignment with its high standards.\\r\\n\\r\\nI aspire to be someone who plays a role in shaping a generation of passionate and capable researchers. I have witnessed how a simple piece of guidance can open new horizons for a learner and inspire confidence in their potential. For that reason, I view scientific mentorship as a noble responsibility\\u2014one that requires both intellectual and emotional commitment. I am ready and enthusiastic to take on that role and grow through it.\",\"second-essay\":\"Dear Team 123,\\r\\n\\r\\nI hope this message finds you well. I understand that the deadline for submitting research proposals has passed and that your team was unable to meet it. While this can be disappointing, I want to assure you that setbacks are a natural part of any meaningful academic journey\\u2014and what matters most is how we respond to them.\\r\\n\\r\\nAt YSJ, we value commitment, collaboration, and resilience. Your participation so far reflects potential, and I believe that with a little push and support, you can still make an excellent contribution. Research isnt only about deadlines\\u2014its about the process of exploration, creativity, and growth. Your ideas matter, and its never too late to bring them to life.\\r\\n\\r\\nI strongly encourage you to regroup, reflect on the direction you want your proposal to take, and make the most of the remaining time. Don\\u2019t hesitate to ask for support from me or other team members\\u2014we\\u2019re here to help you succeed, not to judge your pace.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease share your current thoughts or draft ideas through Discord so we can give feedback and help you finalize your proposal. Remember, your voices are important in this scientific community, and I believe in your ability to complete this task with excellence.\\r\\n\\r\\nLet\\u2019s not aim for perfection\\u2014let\\u2019s aim for progress. Looking forward to seeing your ideas come together.\\r\\n\\r\\nWith support and confidence in you,\\r\\nJudy Mahmoud \\r\\nLead Researcher, YSJ\",\"third-essay\":\"My research background reflects a multidisciplinary approach spanning materials science, renewable energy, and biomedical sciences.\\r\\n\\r\\nI am currently involved in an ongoing project focused on the development of hydrogel-based materials for environmental and biomedical applications. The hydrogel system is being optimized for high water retention and responsiveness to external stimuli, and the work is still in progress, with potential implications in agriculture and drug delivery.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn the area of renewable energy, I have been developing a prototype of a solar chimney integrated with a vertical-axis wind turbine, aiming to harvest both solar thermal and wind energy in a compact design. Early simulations and prototype testing have shown promising results in terms of high efficiency and dual-energy output, demonstrating the potential for off-grid power solutions in remote areas.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn parallel, I have contributed to several research investigations in the biomedical field, including exploratory studies on cancer biology and novel therapeutic approaches. One of my current focuses is on Alzheimer\\u2019s disease, where I have reviewed existing literature and contributed to a research paper proposing gamma-frequency (40 Hz) stimulation as a non-invasive treatment strategy, based on neurophysiological findings. The paper is undergoing peer review.\\r\\n\\r\\nThrough these projects, I have developed skills in experimental design, data analysis, scientific writing, and prototyping. I am passionate about interdisciplinary research that addresses real-world challenges and translates into impactful solutions. My goal is to continue contributing to innovative science that bridges theory and application.\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"2-Page-Summary-Special gg.docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0215\\/drafts\\/2-Page-Summary-Special_gg.docx\",\"size\":248681,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"}]}', '2025-06-30 23:17:35'),
('SYSJ0216', '{\"full-name\":\"Jana Mohmmed \",\"email-address\":\"jenny.23.7.2008@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01067651251\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-07-23\",\"institution\":\"I am still student in high school \",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-25 11:09:20'),
('SYSJ0217', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":\"\",\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-24 22:51:53'),
('SYSJ0218', '{\"full-name\":\"Rana Mohamed\",\"email-address\":\"rana.1624519@stemredsea.moe.edu.eg\",\"contact-number\":\"01205532454\",\"country\":\"Elmonofia Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-10-29\",\"institution\":\"Red Sea STEM \",\"grade-year\":\"grade 11\",\"gpa\":\"3.32\",\"interest\":[\"Computer Science,Data Science,Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering),Mathematics,Robotics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Computer Science\":\"5\",\"Data Science\":\"5\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"5\",\"Mathematics\":\"5\",\"Robotics\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"In Mathematics : B+                           In Computer Science : B+                      \",\"first-essay\":\"Effective mentorship within STEM disciplines blends advanced knowledge and skills with the talent for turning adversity into avenues for growth. As an emerging researcher interested in math, computer science, and robotics, I have done well academically and have enjoyed helping my peers solve difficult concepts\\u2014changing their frustration to fascination. The combination of challenging research contests as well as practical projects has given me concrete ways to motivate future innovators, which is also aligned with YSJ\\u2019s vision of academic excellence coupled with active student engagement.\\r\\n\\r\\nPioneer Academic Program:  \\r\\n\\r\\nMy mathematics research that was part of the Pioneer Academic Program - which is a ive global research initiative - shaped my understanding of how to solve abstract problems. This experience taught me to dissect solutions, something I do now with algorithms and concepts, simplifying them for friends.\\u201d  \\r\\n\\r\\nCompetitions & Awards:  \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cParticipating in international competitions such as Purple Comet (a team-based math modeling competition) and Kangaroo (an advanced problem-solving competition) helped enhance skills critical for reputation. The ability to think under pressure and collaborate is essential in these competitions. It has immensely shaped my capability as well as the way I mentor others.\\u201d  \\r\\n\\r\\nSchool Leadership:  \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u201cMy teachers often say that math and computer science were two subjects where I stood out, making me their go-to tutor for algorithm design or calculus. With such statements lingering from adults there was no choice but to change how one felt towards school. Often described by peers as \\u2018the student who makes others fall in love with math, highlights my charm combined with communication magic.\\u201d\\r\\nThe three components of my mentoring philosophy are: clarity as solving problems in a stepwise manner, creativity as real-world analogy applications such as recursion via Russian dolls, and confidence building through celebrating small wins to build resilience. While at YSJ I plan to set up a robotics research club aimed at helping students leverage theoretical math and computer science concepts within practical projects, aligned with the university\\u2019s learning by doing ethos.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy interdisciplinary approach\\u2014combining engineering, computer science, and environmental sustainability\\u2014matches YSJs innovative and applied spirit. To illustrate, my prior work at the National Institute of Oceanography and Fisheries (NIOF) was a bioelectricity system developed through Chlorella algae, whereby I programmed microbial fuel cell simulations in Python and optimized energy yield by 35%. From this work, I learned to bridge the theory-to-practice gap\\u2014something that I now emphasize when mentoring peers.*\\r\\n\\r\\nSimilarly, my certification from the FAB Lab Robotics Team at my institution (where I tested solar-powered IoT sensors to monitor water) solidified my faith in project-based learning. At YSJ, Id employ available resources to guide students through similar bio-hybrid system development, all in accordance with the universitys focus on global concerns and experiential research.\\r\\n\\r\\nMoreover, YSJs emphasis on collaborative spaces (e.g., maker labs) would allow me to replicate the success of my FAB Lab, inspiring student teams to participate in competitions like RoboNation or Solar Decathlon\\u2014bringing classroom concepts to practical application for a sustainable future.\\r\\nCoaching a Purple Comet team, I noticed their anxiety over time-limited issues. I devised weekly math sprint exercises to improve their speed\\/accuracy, and their scores increased by 40%\\u2014proof that targeted coaching unleashes potential.\\r\\nOne of my classmates was struggling with object-oriented programming in Python. I d visual flowcharts comparing classes to blueprints and objects to houses, which turned into a highly utilized study tool for our grade.\\r\\nBeing part of YSJ would allow me to merge my technical knowledge and passion for mentoring to build the future generation of STEM leaders. My track record of transforming confusion into curiosity\\u2014in research, competitions, or tutoring my peers\\u2014demonstrates that I am ready to fulfill the standards of YSJ while inspiring others to surpass their own expectations. \\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-29 15:06:13'),
('SYSJ0219', '{\"full-name\":\"Rana Essam Abo Ghozail \",\"email-address\":\"onassam068@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01019308165\",\"country\":\"Newvalley \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-10-18\",\"institution\":\"Stem Maadi \",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":\"\",\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-25 03:25:14'),
('SYSJ0220', '{\"full-name\":\"Mahmoud Hussain \",\"email-address\":\"mahmoud.h.academic@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201157693930\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-05-01\",\"institution\":\"Armant Military High School\",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"3.4\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 12:49:02'),
('SYSJ0221', '{\"full-name\":\"Gehad  Ashraf Fathy Taha \",\"email-address\":\"gehadashraf179@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01147226499\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-08-12\",\"institution\":\"Maadi STEM School for girls \",\"grade-year\":\"10\",\"gpa\":\"B+\",\"interest\":[\"Biology\",\"Chemistry\",\"Data Science\",\"Medicine & Public Health\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"grade-previous\":\"Biology A and Chemistry B+\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"9\",\"Chemistry\":\"10\",\"Data Science\":\"5\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"8\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"8\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 13:13:45'),
('SYSJ0224', '{\"full-name\":\"Joudy walid\",\"email-address\":\"joudyw58@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01559678484\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-10-14\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-25 20:06:13'),
('SYSJ0225', '{\"full-name\":\"Soham Sen\",\"email-address\":\"sohamsen15@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+9182407585963\",\"country\":\"India\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-01-15\",\"institution\":\"Delhi Public School Ruby Park\",\"grade-year\":\"Grade 11 (Junior Year)\",\"gpa\":\"4.0 (96.8% average)\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"Computer Science (Grade 9: 100\\/100, Grade 10: 100\\/100), Mathematics (Grade 9: 100\\/100, Grade 10: 93\\/100 - I was unfortunately down with a heavy fever on the day of this exam leading to the sub-par score)\",\"first-essay\":\"1. AI Math from Scratch - A collaborative project with Abhishek Divekar (Senior ML Scientist, Amazon) where we are building content and hosting lectures for high school students looking to get started in AI. The focus is on the mathematical aspects of AI\\/ML which are often overlooked in crash-course style lessons, that are becoming more and more common, causing a lack of necessary rigor.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Online Math Club - Member and Lecturer. I have given lectures on various topics related to graph theory, algorithmic complexity, number theory and combinatorics.\\r\\n\\r\\n3. State Of The Art - AI Olympiad Community - Lecturer and Problem Setter. I curate novel olympiad-style problems focused on the artificial intelligence olympiads (for the IOAI\\/IAIO track) as a IOAI participant myself.\\r\\n\\r\\n4. I also teach mathematics to underprivileged kids at Missionaries of Charity, Premdan twice a week (~4 hrs\\/ week).\",\"second-essay\":\"Hi Team 123,\\r\\n\\r\\nI noticed that you have not yet submitted your research proposal idea. This is critical to move on to the next step. In the case that you are having any problems: perhaps related to the project idea, feasibility, waiting on expert opinions, extenuating circumstances, etc., please do not hesitate to reach out to me. We will figure out a way to work through it together.\\r\\n\\r\\nHoping to see your research proposal soon!\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-03 21:48:42'),
('SYSJ0226', '{\"full-name\":\"Hager Mohamed Abdelhamed Morad \",\"email-address\":\"m28124013@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01147778631\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-08-19\",\"institution\":\"AL-Matania Secondary school \",\"grade-year\":\"Second Secondary \",\"gpa\":\"3.65\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"Through my interest in mathematics, engineering, programming, and artificial intelligence, I was able to develop my skills in logical thinking, problem solving, and organizing ideas scientifically.I always try to apply what Ive learned, whether in school projects or helping my colleagues, especially when something needs explanation or simplification. For example, during a collaborative project, I was able to help the team divide tasks and explain some complex programming concepts in an easy-to-understand way. This allowed us to complete the work with better quality and in less time.My academic goal is to delve deeper into engineering, programming, and artificial intelligence to realize my dream of establishing a major electronics company in Egypt, capable of developing the technological infrastructure, competing with global companies, and positioning Egypt among the leading exporting countries in this field. I also hope to be able to support any student or colleague who has a passion for this field and help them face challenges with confidence, whether in scientific research or technology projects.\",\"second-essay\":\"Hello, I believe that the strength of any team is revealed during the most difficult moments, and this is one of the moments when we can prove to ourselves, before anyone else, that we are capable of accomplishing something we can be proud of. Your presence and ideas are crucial, and every contribution you make will make a huge difference in the strength of our project. Thats why we look forward to sharing your final proposals with us as soon as possible on Discord, so we can unify our vision and achieve the best outcome togetherWere building something that will stand as a testament to our hard work, and each of us truly deserves to be a strong part of it. If you need any support or have an idea you need to flesh out, Im here. Lets get it done and raise our team\'s profile together\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-26 16:34:16'),
('SYSJ0227', '{\"full-name\":\"Yahia Abd El-Aziz \",\"email-address\":\"abdelazizy939@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01148462350\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-08-23\",\"institution\":\"Obour STEM School \",\"grade-year\":\"Senior 26\",\"gpa\":\"3.8\\/4.0\",\"interest\":[\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"10\"},\"grade-previous\":\"B+\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-26 21:18:32'),
('SYSJ0228', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-26 22:03:00'),
('SYSJ0230', '{\"full-name\":\"Analiese Maciel\",\"email-address\":\"macielmgmt@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"2015270177\",\"country\":\"United States\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2004-09-08\",\"institution\":\"Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State University\",\"grade-year\":\"Senior\",\"gpa\":\"3.1\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"8\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"N\\/A\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-27 05:03:20'),
('SYSJ0232', '{\"full-name\":\"Mostafa Mohamed Kamel\",\"email-address\":\"mostafamohamedkamel3900@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01013636738\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-01-01\",\"institution\":\"STEM High Shool for Boys - 6th of October\",\"grade-year\":\"10\",\"gpa\":\"4\",\"interest\":[\"Robotics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Robotics\":\"7\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. This quote captures the heart of scientific mentorship: not merely transmitting information, but inspiring growth through empathy, clarity, and persistence. I strongly resonate with this philosophy, as my own journey in research has not only deepened my technical understanding but also cultivated a passion for helping others navigate their scientific paths.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy experiences at the STEM High School for Boys - 6th of October have been pivotal in preparing me for YSJ\\u2019s high standards. Working on real-world problems\\u2014like designing a soft robot inspired by the mudskipper to traverse the muddy, saline terrain of Lake Manzala\\u2014has required deep interdisciplinary learning across mechanics, material science, and environmental systems. These projects sharpened my analytical skills and exposed me to the iterative nature of research. Yet beyond these technical takeaways, they taught me how essential mentorship is, especially when faced with uncertainty or failure.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs someone who has benefitted from guidance and struggled through knowledge gaps\\u2014especially when quality resources were inaccessible\\u2014I have made it a personal goal to support others who face similar challenges. For example, during our preparations for the RoboCup Egypt 2023 and the subsequent qualification for the global competition in Croatia, I took on a leadership role. Many of my teammates were unfamiliar with machine learning and sensor integration. I started to simplify them the key definitoins and the basics of principles of motor control, making the unfamiliar more approachable. This small step helped spark curiosity and built a stronger foundation for the team to grow from.\",\"second-essay\":\"Hey Team 123,\\r\\n\\r\\nI noticed that your Research Idea Proposal hasnt been submitted yet, and the deadline has already passed. I want to check in\\u2014was there a specific reason for the delay? If you\\u2019ve run into any challenges or roadblocks, please DM me directly. Im here to support you.\\r\\n\\r\\nThat said, its important that we move forward. Please aim to submit your proposal within the next 24 hours, even if it\'s a rough draft. We can always refine it later, but we need a starting point to work from.\\r\\nYou\'re a capable team, and I know you can deliver great work\\u2014let\\u2019s get this back on track.\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-27 14:20:12'),
('SYSJ0234', '{\"full-name\":\"Youssef Farghaly\",\"email-address\":\"youssef.1423064@stemassiut.moe.edu.eg\",\"contact-number\":\"01503502014\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-09-25\",\"institution\":\"Asyut STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"3.7\",\"interest\":[\"Chemistry,Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Chemistry\":\"9\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Chemistry (B+)\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-27 16:48:25'),
('SYSJ0235', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-27 18:36:04'),
('SYSJ0236', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-27 19:47:54'),
('SYSJ0241', '{\"full-name\":\"Mazen Alashry\",\"email-address\":\"mazen.1323025@stemdakahlia.moe.edu.eg\",\"contact-number\":\"01149287184\",\"country\":\"\\u0645\\u0635\\u0631\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-08-15\",\"institution\":\"Dakahlia STEM high school\",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"3.87\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Medicine & Public Health\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"10\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"9\"},\"grade-previous\":\"A\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in scientific research is not simply about conveying knowledge it\\u2019s about unlocking minds, sparking purpose, and transforming uncertainty into discovery.\\r\\n\\r\\nThroughout my academic journey, I\\u2019ve come to embody this philosophy. As a high school researcher from STEM Egypt, I\\u2019ve published peer-reviewed papers \\u2014 including \\u201cThe Impact of Microbiome on Drug Efficiency\\u201d and \\u201cTreating Sickle Cell Disease Using GMOs\\u201d \\u2014 and been accepted into global initiatives like The Junior Academy of the New York Academy of Sciences, IX-YPF Brazil, and the Minerva Research Accelerators, where I serve both as a mentee and a mentor.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy work has explored climate change, environmental innovation, and biomedicine. I\\u2019ve developed an air purification system using industrial waste (CaO) and led a graduation project combining chemistry, hardware, and digital solutions. I also d a mental health app for students living in dorms \\u2014 using AI and VR to turn negative emotions into action.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs a co-leader at Resala STEM Charity Association, I received national awards including a gold medal for top volunteer, a leadership certificate, and recognition in innovation challenges. I also mentor in clubs like FloUra and the Arabic STEM Club, helping students link science to real-world impact.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy academic goal is to advance in biomedical research and  inclusive platforms for youth innovation. My mentoring goal is to empower students not just to understand science \\u2014 but to feel they belong in it.\\r\\n\\r\\nYSJ\\u2019s commitment to excellence and student-led inquiry aligns perfectly with these goals. I\\u2019m excited to bring my interdisciplinary background and global experiences to help guide emerging researchers. Whether simplifying statistical analysis or helping peers shape publishable hypotheses, I\\u2019ve seen firsthand how the right question, asked at the right time, can change a student\\u2019s path.\\r\\n\\r\\nAt YSJ, I aim to serve as a bridge \\u2014 connecting students to science, to opportunity, and most importantly, to belief in themselves.\",\"second-essay\":\"\\r\\nHey Team 123 \\ud83d\\udc4b,\\r\\n\\r\\nI hope youre all doing well. I wanted to quickly reach out regarding the Research Idea Proposal, which was due recently.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs of now, I haven\\u2019t received your submission \\u2014 and I understand that things can get overwhelming, but timely communication and commitment are core parts of our research culture at YSJ. Missing deadlines not only delays your own progress, but it also affects the pacing of the entire cohort.\\r\\n\\r\\nThat said, I believe in your potential, and I know you\\u2019re capable of producing something great. Please prioritize wrapping up the proposal within the next 24 hours. If you\\u2019re facing any blockers \\u2014 technical, conceptual, or logistical \\u2014 don\\u2019t hesitate to reach out. I\\u2019m here to support, not to pressure.\\r\\n\\r\\nLet\\u2019s get back on track and make this project something you\\u2019ll be proud of. Looking forward to your  soon!\\r\\n\\r\\nKeep pushing \\ud83d\\udca1\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-28 00:01:02'),
('SYSJ0242', '{\"full-name\":\"Nour Anter\",\"email-address\":\"anternour88@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01558659984\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-10-01\",\"institution\":\"Stem October 11th district School\",\"grade-year\":\"g12\",\"gpa\":\"3.31\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"BIOLOGY: B+\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 13:10:04'),
('SYSJ0244', '{\"full-name\":\"Haneen Hossam \",\"email-address\":\"hosamhaneen92@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01203166197\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-05-01\",\"institution\":\"Ismailia STEM High school \",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"3.82\",\"interest\":[\"Data Science\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Data Science\":\"5\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"7\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\" I dont study them in my school \",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-05 01:00:52'),
('SYSJ0245', '{\"full-name\":\"Salma abdalluh \",\"email-address\":\"badrsalma926@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01158530093\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-07-16\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-28 19:10:26'),
('SYSJ0246', '{\"full-name\":\"Yasmine Asaad\",\"email-address\":\"jmickmore@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"00201005291053\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"1998-03-01\",\"institution\":\"Faculty of Medicine, Zagazig University \",\"grade-year\":\"2021\",\"gpa\":\"92.8%\",\"interest\":[\"Environmental Science,Medicine & Public Health\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Environmental Science\":\"5\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"10\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Public health: 295\\/300   Medicine: 92.8%\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-28 19:26:02'),
('SYSJ0249', '{\"full-name\":\"Ahmed Mohammed Abdelkhalek Mohammed\",\"email-address\":\"ahmedmoalkhalek105@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201024013838\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2006-05-10\",\"institution\":\"Applied Technology School for Nuclear Energy in El-Dabaa\",\"grade-year\":\"G12\",\"gpa\":\"3.97\\/4.00\",\"interest\":[\"Computer Science,Mathematics,Physics & Astrophysics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Computer Science\":\"6\",\"Mathematics\":\"7\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"10\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Fourth Year of High School>> Nuclear Physics: 30\\/30 - - Radiological Physics (Radiation Protection): 30\\/30 - - Advanced Mathematics: 40\\/40 - - Communcation Systems: 20\\/20 - - Electronics of Radiation Detectors:19\\/20 - - - - Transcripts>> https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/drive\\/folders\\/1wf9hj_fu3Qua7k81d7FxIcOxBgwbSM2t?usp=sharing \",\"first-essay\":\"\\tIt\\u2019s all about that first paper. Based on my research experience (4 years since my G10 at my 5-year school), when faced with a vast pool of resources, no doubt first-timers feel frustrated and overwhelmed, and may try to tackle it all at once without knowing which resource or course to start with. That\\u2019s one point. Another is zeroing in on the right and creative ideas, which depends on learning the basics and fully understanding the current argument before challenging or improving it. Ambitious projects might demand extensive study, but I\\u2019ve handled that with a clear order and strategy I still use with my peers in class and through Pioneer Academic Research.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\tThis was just an introduction to the vast, sometimes vague realm of scientific research, but it\\u2019s extremely different from pure theory to experimental analytical work. Based on my real experiences (not just my interests), I know mentees from STEM, Thanaweya Amma, or Applied Nuclear Technology School (my school) will face similar challenges, of course, in this realm, so we have a common ground.\\r\\nMy first major real project was at the NASA Space Apps Alexandria event. With a background in computational astrophysics, complex analysis, till Calculus-III, linear algebra, data science, and quantum computing, creating a data-science\\/computational-physics program that analyzes IMF vectors from spacecraft to measure reconnection frequency. We ranked first as a global nominee, placing in the top 3.69% out of 12,500 international projects.\\r\\nMoreover, I won the 1st Grand Award at ISEF 2025 and took Gold in Embedded Systems at BASEF, out of 2,500 global teams. I also placed 1st in Africa\\/Egypt\\/Middle East at Physics Brawl 2024 (top 0.5% of 1,584 teams).\\r\\n\\r\\nIn mentorship and research,\\r\\n1. I was one of four (\\u22481.5%) to earn a full-tuition scholarship for Indigo\\u2019s elite six-month, one-on-one Researcher Program (a \\\\$5,000 award plus two UCSB credits).\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Founded the first quantum-computing club in the MENA region with El-Hossieny, guiding 50+ students + Qiskit-based projects. \\r\\n\\r\\n3. Vice president of the ATSNEE Physics Club, I led 250 students in quantum\\/nuclear physics.\\r\\nConducting research in 3D Quantum Gravity Partitions under Prof. Koroteev at UC Berkeley (INST 099, 4 credits through Oberlin). \\r\\n\\r\\n4. Led Relaunched Academy as VP, organizing a 5\\u20136-month workshop series for 50+ high schoolers across six STEM fields (including nuclear and biomedical engineering).  \\r\\n\\r\\nSo yeah, that\\u2019s most of the info. I\\u2019ll follow up by email with my supplementary materials, previous research work.\",\"second-essay\":\"Dear Xenons (I just want to change their name from 123 to Xenon, it is much better),\\r\\n\\r\\n\\tWhat\\u2019s up, guys? I hope you are doing so well with the assigned materials we have discussed in our last session, which were [Hardy\\u2013Ramanujan Partition Function Proof, Quantum Statistical Mechanics Approach in Counting Partitions, and using Quantum Monte Carlo simulations in modeling a non-interacting system of bosons & fermions]. Those materials are essential in order to draft an outline and brainstorm a research project idea based on your last preferences, which we have tackled together in terms of the direction for your analytical approach.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\tThis is not a kind of freaking out I just want to tell you that in order to navigate into those materials you must be familiar with 1. Complex Analysis 2. Proofs of Discrete\\/Combinatorial Mathematics 3. Study Introduction to Applied Mathematics & Computational Science, followed by the MITx \\u201cComputational Data Science in Physics I\\u2013III\\u201d if this is what makes you frustrated or don\\u2019t feel okay with the materials. However, if this is not the case, I\\u2019m available every day from 6:00 PM to 5:00 AM Cairo time, which corresponds to 11:00 AM to 10:00 PM U.S. time.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\tWe can set a meeting next Monday (5 days from now), but I just want to make sure that you have read those materials and have written some ideas with their outlines in order to discuss them together, so that we can write your proposed work in LaTeX at your convenience. And of course, you can reach out to me or even call me at any time if there is a concept you don\\u2019t understand.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\tFinally, just a reminder that the proposal is your guidance into your research experience, and it is the main resource that would make you feel okay in terms of following up and the feasibility of your project, so making such a detailed one and discussing its applicability and time frame together would make everything easier for you and for me to set you some course to take in the available time. In other words, you have about 5 days in order to study the assigned materials and join group sessions with me if any explanations or guidance are needed, and it\\u2019s okay, at the end, we are gonna build it together over this week.\\\\\\r\\n\\r\\n\\tThanks for your invaluable time, our great researcher! I see your passion and enthusiasm in your discussions and assignments, and you really have great potential and are gonna be some great folks in the future. It\\u2019s just about taking the initiative at work.  I\\u2019ll share a quote my professor used to say in our meetings to help me focus on what\\u2019s in my hands and avoid distractions: Richard Feynman said, \\u201cShut up and calculate.\\u201d It actually worked for me, though I didn\\u2019t have the finesse we have now, so we won\\u2019t take it too literally. :)\\r\\n\\r\\nWe have a deal, then! See you tomorrow with any questions!\\r\\n\",\"third-essay\":\"Certifications: [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/drive\\/folders\\/1WKL2IdI9myI_Vi48yG3MJYIsuAc7fVem?usp=sharing]\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Resume  \\r\\n   [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1ehar-MaL8xtwaVTz3AOLx60PKhnVowgY\\/view?usp=sharing]\\r\\n\\r\\n2. I achieved the 1st Grand Award at ISEF 2025 and Gold Medal in Embedded Systems among 2,500 BASEF teams with a drone for 3D radiation mapping & radioactive source spectroscopy & decontamination.  \\r\\n   o Research Plan [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/18HnICUWUKOVSuceyDo-ZBckD2jSu4fNR\\/view?usp=sharing]  \\r\\n   o Project Documentation [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1VVk1nBTBQcmweEn5x_5P_8MXpgQMofO6\\/view?usp=sharing]  \\r\\n   o Research Paper [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1aifmkX0Flq-BzvkkrPVBzmnFa9DErSh-\\/view?usp=drive_link]  \\r\\n   o Business Materials [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/drive\\/folders\\/1xSp6baVJUYUdnTPf0XqRdT3HVqri6c2V?usp=sharing]\\r\\n\\r\\n3. Global Nominee at NASA Space Apps Alexandria 2023 hackathon (Top 3.69% of 12,500).  \\r\\n   o GitHub: https:\\/\\/github.com\\/qhmedhazem\\/plasma_knights  \\r\\n   o Detailed Project Portfolio [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1wiXXGawJp1ozMSTwhjGm1YwP5LqLz1LY\\/view]  \\r\\n   o NASA Space Apps Details [https:\\/\\/www.spaceappschallenge.org\\/2023\\/find-a-team\\/plasma-knights\\/?tab=details]\\r\\n\\r\\n4. Founder of the 1st Quantum Computing Branch\\/Club in the MENA region with El-Hossieny led 50+ students via lectures & labs in linear algebra, coding & Qiskit research projects.  \\r\\n   [https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1acMvqiSQNxwY9GnMYdeMMtkC50yjTogY\\/view?usp=sharing]\\r\\n\\r\\n5. 1st place in Africa\\/Egypt\\/Middle East at Physics Brawl 2024, ranked top 0.5% globally among 1,584 teams.\\r\\n\\r\\n6. Sele-cted as one of four (\\u22481.5%) to receive a full-tuition scholarship for Indigo\\u2019s six-month, one-to-one Researcher Program with Prof. Aditya (Harvard astrophysicist) \\\\$5,000 + 20 h mentorship + 2 UCSB credits.\\r\\n\\r\\n7. Awarded a fully credited international summer course in quantum computing through QWorld, Alamein International University (AIU) & the Alexandria Quantum Computing Group (AleQCG).\\r\\n\\r\\n8. CEO\\/Co-Founder of the ATSNEE Physics Club led 250 students in quantum\\/nuclear physics.\\r\\n\\r\\n9. Certified Trainer (B-Category) by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.\\r\\n\\r\\n10. Currently researching an Analytic\\u2013Computational Synthesis of Partition-Function and VMC\\/DMC QSMs Simulations for Non-interacting Bosonic\\/Fermionic Harmonic Oscillators under Prof. Koroteev, UC Berkeley INST 099\\u20144 Oberlin College credits.\\r\\n\\r\\n11. Led Relaunched Academy as Vice President, organized a 5\\u20136-month, multi-session online workshop series for 50+ high schoolers.\\r\\n\\r\\n12. Part-timer & led sustainability workshops for 30K+ youth, engaging 1.2K+ internationals at AIESEC Luxor & Media-Doc\\u2019s EGYouth4Climate campaign.\\r\\n\\r\\n13. Logicae-Science LSWP \\r\\n\\r\\n14. Completed a 2-semester IBM-sponsored quantum course, earned a 110% grade & \\\\$1,195 scholarship, applied Qiskit, Python & linear algebra in lab & project work.\"}', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"Research_Proposal_outlining__the_planned_methods (2).pdf\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0249\\/drafts\\/Research_Proposal_outlining__the_planned_methods__2_.pdf\",\"size\":349118,\"type\":\"application\\/pdf\"}],\"commented_files\":[{\"name\":\"Copy of Comparing piston, turboprop, turbojet, and turbofan engines in terms of mechanism, fuel consumption, optimal cruising conditions, and opportunities for future development (1).docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0249\\/drafts\\/Copy_of_Comparing_piston__turboprop__turbojet__and_turbofan_engines_in_terms_of_mechanism__fuel_consumption__optimal_cruising_conditions__and_opportunities_for_future_development__1_.docx\",\"size\":700875,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"}],\"additional_files\":[{\"name\":\"Ahmed M.Abdelkhalek-Sh.pdf\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0249\\/drafts\\/Ahmed_M.Abdelkhalek-Sh.pdf\",\"size\":281166,\"type\":\"application\\/pdf\"}]}', '2025-07-02 11:12:17'),
('SYSJ0250', '{\"full-name\":\"veronica tharwat \",\"email-address\":\"jhvlsf@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201284097723\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-01-26\",\"institution\":\"Sharkya STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"3.64\",\"interest\":[\"Computer Science,Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering),Environmental Science,Mathematics,Robotics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Computer Science\":\"4\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"4\",\"Environmental Science\":\"6\",\"Mathematics\":\"5\",\"Robotics\":\"4\"},\"grade-previous\":\"grade 10\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 14:34:38'),
('SYSJ0251', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-29 16:04:13'),
('SYSJ0253', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 15:42:14'),
('SYSJ0256', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 12:12:49'),
('SYSJ0257', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 12:13:03'),
('SYSJ0259', '{\"full-name\":\"Manar Ahmed Abd Al Naeem \",\"email-address\":\"134manar12344@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"1070929963\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-07-15\",\"institution\":\"High school students \",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Chemistry,Economics,Education,Environmental Science,International Relations & Government,Medicine & Public Health,Neuroscience & Neurobiology,Physics & Astrophysics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"5\",\"Chemistry\":\"5\",\"Economics\":\"5\",\"Education\":\"5\",\"Environmental Science\":\"8\",\"International Relations & Government\":\"5\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"5\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in scientific research is not just about mastering technical concepts\\r\\n it\\u2019s about guiding and inspiring students through uncertainty, challenge, and discovery. Throughout my journey, I\\u2019ve developed a strong passion for tackling future global challenges, particularly in the fields of health and environmental sustainability. This passion has shaped both my research direction and my approach to mentorship.\\r\\nRather than focusing solely on technical achievement, I aim to use science as a tool for solving real-world problems. My research interests lie in exploring innovative, affordable, and scalable solutions to persistent issues like chronic disease management and waste pollution. These experiences have helped me appreciate the importance of interdisciplinary thinking, ethical responsibility, and resilience in research.\\r\\nMy mentoring goal is to  a supportive space where young researchers are empowered to ask bold questions, explore creatively, and embrace failure as a path to deeper learning. I believe the YSJ model with its focus on student-led inquiry, global collaboration, and scientific integrity perfectly aligns with this vision. Through YSJ, I hope to help students grow not just as researchers, but as leaders and problem-solvers in the face of tomorrow\\u2019s challenges.\\r\\nOne memorable experience involved mentoring a group of students overwhelmed by a complex environmental project. They struggled to define a research question and felt lost in the process. Together, we broke down the topic into manageable parts, explored existing literature, and developed a testable hypothesis. As they gained confidence and clarity, I saw how a shift in mindset can reignite curiosity and motivation.\\r\\nMentorship, to me, is about nurturing both the scientific and human potential within each student. It\\u2019s about showing them that science is not just a subject, but a way to build a better future especially in times that demand bold, sustainable innovation.\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"second-essay\":\"Hey Team 123!\\r\\nI noticed the Research Idea Proposal deadline was missed . I understand things can get overwhelming, but we need to stay on track.\\r\\nLet\\u2019s prioritize this: please submit a draft version of your idea by tomorrow 5 PM GMT it doesn\\u2019t have to be perfect. I\\u2019m here if you need help refining it.\\r\\nRemember, the earlier we start, the more feedback we can incorporate and that\\u2019s how great research gets built. Let\\u2019s make this happen! \\r\\n\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 13:12:09'),
('SYSJ0260', '{\"full-name\":\"Yasmin Amr Hemed\",\"email-address\":\"Yasmin.1724563@stemismailia.moe.edu.eg\",\"contact-number\":\"01015538654\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-04-20\",\"institution\":\"Ismailia Stem High School\",\"grade-year\":\"G11\",\"gpa\":\"4.00\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"A \",\"first-essay\":\"ytr\",\"second-essay\":\"uy\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-02 18:06:09');
INSERT INTO `application_drafts` (`user_id`, `data`, `files`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('SYSJ0261', '{\"full-name\":\"Omar Tamer Nabil ElNahas\",\"email-address\":\"omarteto145omp@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201275333046\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-05-24\",\"institution\":\"Dakahlia STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"G11\",\"gpa\":\"3.93\",\"interest\":[\"Computer Science,Medicine & Public Health,Physics & Astrophysics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Computer Science\":\"7\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"5\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"In the Computer Science I got at the first semester A and at the second semester I got B+ and the Physics I got also A at it , for the Medicine & Public Health , I do not have a subject with this name, but the subject which is similar to it is Biology and I got A at it\",\"first-essay\":\"As a student researcher, I have always assisted other students and junior peers in overcoming the obstacles of scientific research. For example, during the time when our school had an across-the-campus science project, I assisted a group of Grade 9 students who were unable to form a testable hypothesis for their environment-themed project. Rather than giving them answers, I took them through how to break down a broad subject into manageable questions, showed them the concepts of experimental design, and asked them to think analytically about the cause and effect relationship. By the last sessions, not only had they developed a good hypothesis, but they were actually looking forward to doing the experiment  a switch from confusion to interest that I found absolutely fulfilling.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn a different situation, I instructed fellow teachers who were presenting a presentation at a national science fair to understand statistical software with which they would be working to analyze their data. They were frustrated with such terms as standard deviation and correlation coefficient, but following one to one instruction in which I used simple analogies and common examples, they felt comfortable and were able to present their data successfully.\\r\\n\\r\\nThese interactions imparted the value of patience, specificity, and enthusiasm in mentoring  the same values that I feel encompass YSJs purpose. I look forward to continuing to grow as a mentor through helping others discover the same enthusiasm for science that I have.\",\"second-essay\":\"Hey Team 123,\\r\\nI hope youre all doing okay. I noticed that your research idea proposal hasnt been submitted yet, and I just wanted to check in. I know things can get overwhelming, but your proposal is a crucial step that sets the foundation for everything ahead.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf youre stuck or need feedback, I\\u2019m here to support you  just let me know. That said, we\\u2019re past the deadline, and it\\u2019s important we catch up quickly to stay aligned with the program timeline. Try to finalize and submit it within the next 24 hours so we can start reviewing it and moving forward.\\r\\n\\r\\nYouve all got great potential, and I\\u2019m excited to see where your ideas lead  let\\u2019s get this done. \\r\\n\\r\\n [Your Name]\\r\\nYSJ Senior Researcher\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 15:25:16'),
('SYSJ0262', '[]', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"Research summary..PNG\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0262\\/drafts\\/Research_summary..PNG\",\"size\":108259,\"type\":\"image\\/png\"}]}', '2025-06-30 16:42:55'),
('SYSJ0265', '{\"full-name\":\"Sama Mohamed \",\"email-address\":\"s78724462@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01551345906\",\"country\":\"Egyptian \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-05-07\",\"institution\":\"Egypt\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 17:10:25'),
('SYSJ0266', '{\"full-name\":\"Afaf Kamel\",\"email-address\":\"afafkamelrezk@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201153921800\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2005-06-07\",\"institution\":\"Mansoura university\",\"grade-year\":\"sophomore\",\"gpa\":\"4.53\\\\5\",\"interest\":[\"Architecture,Biology,Chemistry\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Architecture\":\"6\",\"Biology\":\"10\",\"Chemistry\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"NA\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 17:39:55'),
('SYSJ0267', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 17:41:02'),
('SYSJ0268', '{\"full-name\":\"Abdallah Amr \",\"email-address\":\"abdo1872009@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01016985021\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-07-18\",\"institution\":\"Alexandria STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"10\",\"gpa\":\"3.8\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"3\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"7\",\"Mathematics\":\"9\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"10\"},\"grade-previous\":\"A grade in physics and mathmatics\",\"first-essay\":\"in our life, we can fail many times but this fails are considered success and progress. the experience you will learn from your situations that happens to you daily are your earn from life. As i am stem student and in holiday, now i am helping people which want to join my school, for example, i with my friends made group on whatsapp and give some advices and tricks to help peaple which want to join our school to pass entrance exam. this helps and advices that i serve for this ambitious students make me happy and in want to help more people. because this feeling make me understand that i can help many people and remind me with people that helped me to reach my success and join my school . YSJ is more than just a publication\\u2014its a comprehensive research education ecosystem: students learn by doing research, supporting each other, and publishing in a peer\\u2011reviewed format. for me YSJ program will help me a lot this days in improve my career and my skills in scientific research. improving my scientific research skills will help me in my academic goals like win competitions related to scientific research like ISEF competition, help me in my school project and give me some confidence in my self. \\r\\n\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"my research background is relative simple. I have made a project with my friends in school before about generating energy from and store it to be usable after.\\r\\nour project name is aeornovea . its idea is to generate electricity from wind by change mechanical energy of wind into electrical energy. this process occurs by horizontal axis wind turbine and the invention in the project is the design of it and system of storing energy. i have also shared in another project to solve one of egypts grand challenge: traffic loads and arid areas.\\r\\nto solve this problem we make bridge that can be on rivers and big lakes as . this bridge can be opened by retractable way as it divide into four parts: two fixed parts and another two movable parts. movable parts go on fixed parts to allow the moving of ships in the river.\\r\\nfrom my childhood, i love stars and planets and this is my nature. so from a year i hear about IAAC competition(International astronomy and astrophysics competition). i share in this competition and gain the fifth place on my country. this competition enhanced my research background in this filed. finally, I hope that i will be accepted in YSJ program and I promise I will give any effort demanded to benefit small youths and benefit my self from this annully program.\",\"hours_commitment\":\"10\",\"time_blocks\":\"none\",\"hear_about\":\"from my friend\"}', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"12106-2.pdf\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0268\\/drafts\\/6869863033786_12106-2.pdf\",\"size\":641127,\"type\":\"application\\/pdf\"}],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 20:31:00'),
('SYSJ0269', '{\"full-name\":\"Mohamed fady\",\"email-address\":\"zakyfady78@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+20 1095010954\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-04-18\",\"institution\":\"Gharbiya high STEM school\",\"grade-year\":\"g 12 \",\"gpa\":\"3.7\\/4\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Environmental Science\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"8\",\"Environmental Science\":\"9\"},\"grade-previous\":\"biology : 93%            Environmental Science : 96%\",\"first-essay\":\"mentorship in scientific research goes beyond sharing knowledge it is about inspiring young minds to question explore and persist through challenges throughout my academic journey i have developed a strong foundation in scientific research especially in designing experiments analyzing data critically and communicating results clearly these skills have prepared me to guide students not just in the technical aspects of research but also in building resilience and curiosity my academic goal is to continue advancing in research while nurturing a new generation of scientists who are not afraid to ask bold questions as a mentor i aim to  an environment where students feel supported valued and encouraged to think independently ysj diverse international community and structured mentorship program offer the perfect platform to achieve this the collaborative environment access to global perspectives and focus on publishing quality research would empower me to help young researchers reach their potential for example i once supported a group of high school students in developing a science fair project on renewable energy they struggled with designing a feasible experiment so i worked with them to simplify their research question identify measurable variables and build a realistic prototype seeing their confidence grow and their excitement return was deeply rewarding in another instance i helped peers struggling with statistical analysis by organizing short study sessions which not only improved their understanding but also sparked new ideas for their projects through these experiences i realized that mentorship is about guiding students to see challenges as opportunities and to appreciate the beauty of scientific discovery joining ysj as a senior researcher would allow me to continue this mission on a larger scale supporting young scientists worldwide as they explore learn and innovate\\r\\n\",\"second-essay\":\"hey team 123 i know we all have a lot on our plates but we really need to get our research idea proposal wrapped up as soon as possible missing the deadline can slow us down and i truly believe your ideas have great potential lets put our heads together finalize the draft and get it submitted today if anyone is stuck or needs help please share here and we can sort it out together we got this\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 18:23:03'),
('SYSJ0271', '{\"full-name\":\"Reem Mohamed Abo Elaa \",\"email-address\":\"reemmohammed200920092009@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01099705200\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"birth-date\":\"2008-04-27\",\"institution\":\"Omar Soliman language school \",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"4\",\"interest\":[\"Biology\",\"Computer Science\",\"Medicine & Public Health\",\"Psychology\"],\"grade-previous\":\"Biology:A+, psychology:A+, computer science A+\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in scientific research requires not only a deep understanding of complex concepts, but also the ability to translate those ideas into real solutions\\u2014and to guide others to do the same. Through my work on two research-based projects, MemoCare and Batoot, I\\u2019ve had the opportunity to apply computer science and AI to address challenges in healthcare and mental wellness.\\r\\n\\r\\nMemoCare, an app I co-developed for Alzheimer\\u2019s patients, uses reminders, visual cues, and family engagement tools to support memory and daily functioning. In this project, I explored how AI can personalize experiences for patients, while also supporting caregivers and doctors with structured medical information. As I led parts of the design process, I mentored my team in understanding both the medical context and how to translate it into accessible tech features. This showed me the power of combining empathy, research, and scientific clarity when guiding others.\\r\\n\\r\\nSimilarly, Batoot, a stress management app for youth, was based on behavioral science and neuroscience. I helped the team integrate AI-driven suggestions and calming techniques, and when one teammate struggled to understand the science behind stress pathways, I broke down the research in simple terms, linking it to everyday examples. That moment reminded me how mentoring is also about making others feel capable and connected to their work.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy academic goal is to become a doctor who merges AI and medicine to serve both physicians and patients. I want to mentor young researchers to see the potential of interdisciplinary work, especially in using technology to solve real human problems. YSJ\\u2019s commitment to advanced science and mentorship aligns perfectly with my vision, and I believe it would be the ideal place to grow as both a scientist and a guide for others.\",\"second-essay\":\"Dear team 123\\r\\nI noticed the research idea proposal hasnt been submitted yet . I know how can be difficult sometimes. I believe in your potential, your ideas and your Passion .you\\u2019ve got what it takes to make an impact. Let\\u2019s give this final push together!I\\u2019m here to support you every step of the way. I can help in any thing (feedback, brainstorming, or just someone to talk it through with) .Don\\u2019t stress about making it perfect\\u2014just get something down and we can build on it together \",\"third-essay\":\"Although I have not yet published formal research papers, I have been actively involved in research-based projects that reflect both my scientific curiosity and interdisciplinary mindset. My core interests lie in computer science, medicine, and psychology, and I\\u2019ve explored how these fields intersect through original project ideas I helped conceptualize and develop.\\r\\n\\r\\nOne of my major projects is MemoCare, a concept app aimed at supporting Alzheimer\\u2019s patients, caregivers, and their families. Although it has not yet been published or launched publicly, I conducted in-depth research into memory-related conditions, exploring how AI and reminders could aid in daily tasks and emotional support. I also investigated stress-relief techniques and how visual memory can be enhanced through personalized content. This research guided the structure and user features of the proposed app.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn a similar way, Batoot is a concept project focused on youth stress management. While also not yet public or published, it was developed using scientific literature and behavioral studies. I researched emotional regulation techniques, meditation science, and the cognitive effects of music and daily routines. These insights helped shape the core ideas and design of the app.\\r\\n\\r\\nThrough both experiences, I developed strong skills in hypothesis formulation, scientific reading, critical thinking, and applying research to real-world challenges. Even though I haven\\u2019t reached the stage of publication, I view these projects as valuable research journeys that allowed me to work like a young scientist\\u2014asking questions, testing ideas, and aiming to make a meaningful impact.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs I pursue a future in medicine, I am committed to contributing to the field through research. Joining YSJ would be a powerful step forward\\u2014helping me refine my skills, collaborate with other aspiring researchers, and work toward publishing formal studies in areas that truly matter.\\r\\n\",\"hours_commitment\":\"12\",\"time_blocks\":\"From 10 July to 10 September \",\"hear_about\":\"A friend \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"10\",\"Computer Science\":\"9\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"9\",\"Psychology\":\"7\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":{\"8\":{\"name\":\"Black and White Corporate Resume_20250626_145002_0000.pdf\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0271\\/drafts\\/686980bb33bb0_Black_and_White_Corporate_Resume_20250626_145002_0000.pdf\",\"size\":479115,\"type\":\"application\\/pdf\"}}}', '2025-07-05 19:44:59'),
('SYSJ0272', '{\"full-name\":\"Zhanat Abshukir \",\"email-address\":\"abshukirzhanat07@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+77471278857\",\"country\":\"Kazakhstan \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-11-05\",\"institution\":\"NIS ChBd in Turkistan \",\"grade-year\":\"2026\",\"gpa\":\"4.8\",\"interest\":[\"Environmental Science,Medicine & Public Health,Psychology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Environmental Science\":\"9\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"10\",\"Psychology\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"N\\/A\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 20:00:03'),
('SYSJ0273', '{\"full-name\":\"Mariam Mohammad Farrag\",\"email-address\":\"mariammfarrag2050@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01032624022\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2010-01-24\",\"institution\":\"Maadi STEM school\",\"grade-year\":\"G11\",\"gpa\":\"4\",\"interest\":[\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering),Mathematics,Robotics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"5\",\"Mathematics\":\"10\",\"Robotics\":\"10\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Mathematics A TOTAL but we dont have Engineering field and robotics in the school but i take courses in them\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 21:34:34'),
('SYSJ0274', '{\"full-name\":\"Ebram Hany Ibrahim louka\",\"email-address\":\"ibramhanyibrahemlouka@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01005745849\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-06-22\",\"institution\":\"STEM 6th of October - High School for Boys\",\"grade-year\":\"10\",\"gpa\":\"4.0\",\"interest\":[\"Physics & Astrophysics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"A \",\"first-essay\":\"As I am a physics major, I like to apply the Feynmann technique, the says: if you cannot explain something, you do not understand it enough. So, from my academic goals is to reach a deeper comprehension of the materials I am presenting through explaining it to others. Moreover, as I am currently preparing to participate in IPhO competition, I have already covered most of the necessary topics that I would need. I am also a part of the physics club community at my school, where we have already finished classical mechanics and covered some of calculus 1.\\r\\nAnd from my mentoring goals is to foster independent thinking by encouraging them to ask how and why, not just accepting facts and explain how YSJ gives some a platform to publish and take ownership of their work which enforces direct self-learning.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nAnd from my mentorship experiences:\\r\\nAs my school accepts both Arabic and English learners, some of the Arabic students struggle with the English lifestyle of the school. Consequently, my English teacher arranged an English proficiency test, where the stronger English students help the weaker ones. Frankly, I aced that test easily, while others hardly passed half the questions. As I was one from the top 3 in my class, I was requested to tutor the weakest one. On our first session, he complained a lot about he mixes the past, present perfect, and present perfect continuous tenses. I then, began explaining how the present perfect focuses on the action and not the time and how it relates actions in the past with the present, then I gave this example to differentiate between past and present perfect: I have bought a villa - I bought a villa in 2009. What clear difference do you see? I asked. He replied: The present perfect in the first sentence focuses on the action of buying the villa and does not specify a time, while the second focus on the buying the villa in a specific point in time (2009). Then I explained how the present perfect continuous focus on the duration of an action that started in the past and continues till the present. Then I compared both tenses: I have been working all morning - I have eaten a cake. I explained how the first sentence focuses on the actions duration, and the second focuses on the action itself of eating the cake. \",\"second-essay\":\"Hey team 123!\\r\\nI have noticed the Research idea proposal deadline has passed and I have not seen your submission yet. While we all have busy schedules, meeting deadlines is a necessary part of the research process. Not only for your teams progress but also for keeping the YSJ timeline on track. \\r\\nPlease aim to submit your proposal by [Friday 5pm]. If you are struggling with something or running into issues, whether it is idea development or coordination, please, do not hesitate to reach out. I am here to support you and help you troubleshoot.\\r\\nWe all are really excited and looking forward to seeing what you have been working on!\\r\\n [Ebram Hany], YSJ Senior Researcher\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 23:39:19'),
('SYSJ0275', '{\"full-name\":\"Layla Amr\",\"email-address\":\"laylaamrmahmoud1f@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201024313624\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-09-06\",\"institution\":\"Alfarouk Language School\",\"grade-year\":\"Grade 9\",\"gpa\":\"3.4 \",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"9\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"6\",\"Mathematics\":\"9\",\"Psychology\":\"7\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Not applicable \",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 19:27:21'),
('SYSJ0276', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 21:55:38'),
('SYSJ0277', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"Greywater Reuse Egypt.pdf\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0277\\/drafts\\/Greywater_Reuse_Egypt.pdf\",\"size\":23676,\"type\":\"application\\/pdf\"},{\"name\":\"poster (Dead cell revival).pdf\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0277\\/drafts\\/poster__Dead_cell_revival_.pdf\",\"size\":932231,\"type\":\"application\\/pdf\"}]}', '2025-07-02 19:54:52'),
('SYSJ0278', '{\"full-name\":\"Flopater Eshak\",\"email-address\":\"flopatereshak@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201033756139\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-01-06\",\"institution\":\"future\",\"grade-year\":\"10\",\"gpa\":\"4.8\",\"interest\":[\"Arts,Classics,Computer Science,Data Science,Education,Mathematics,Psychology,Robotics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Arts\":\"5\",\"Classics\":\"5\",\"Computer Science\":\"5\",\"Data Science\":\"5\",\"Education\":\"5\",\"Mathematics\":\"4\",\"Psychology\":\"2\",\"Robotics\":\"1\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-06-30 22:06:59'),
('SYSJ0280', '{\"full-name\":\"Menna Allah Ahmed Hamed \",\"email-address\":\"menna972020@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01276203226\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-08-31\",\"institution\":\"Al-Huwayati \",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"90\\u066a\",\"interest\":[\"Psychology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Psychology\":\"9\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 19:49:56'),
('SYSJ0283', '{\"full-name\":\"Salma Fahmy Mokhtar Fahmy Sherif \",\"email-address\":\"salmafahmy504@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01067521450\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-09-09\",\"institution\":\"Stem Red Sea \",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"2.7\",\"interest\":[\"Chemistry,Medicine & Public Health,Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Chemistry\":\"6\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"9\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"2.7\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 03:00:18'),
('SYSJ0285', '{\"full-name\":\"Fares Ramadan\",\"email-address\":\"faresramadan2725@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+963933278882\",\"country\":\"Syria \\/ Canada \",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-07-25\",\"institution\":\"Al-Saade High School \",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"98%\",\"interest\":[\"Biology\",\"Chemistry\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"8\",\"Chemistry\":\"5\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Biology 290\\/300 chemistry 200\\/200 physics 390\\/400 \",\"first-essay\":\"One time, my friend was struggling with balancing chemical equations in chemistry class. They found it confusing, so I broke it down step by step. I used simple examples, like the reaction between hydrogen and oxygen to form water, and showed them how to count atoms on both sides. Seeing their face light up when they finally got it was awesome!  \\r\\n\\r\\nAnother example was during a group project on Newton\\u2019s Laws. Some teammates didn\\u2019t understand how forces work, so I used everyday examples\\u2014like pushing a chair (Newton\\u2019s First Law) or kicking a soccer ball (Newton\\u2019s Second Law). Making it relatable helped them grasp the concepts better, and we ended up having fun experimenting with different scenarios.  \\r\\n\\r\\nI also helped a classmate who was stuck on genetics problems in biology. I drew Punnett squares and explained dominant vs. recessive traits using eye color as an example. Once they saw how traits pass from parents to offspring, they became more interested and even started asking deeper questions.  \\r\\n\\r\\nThese experiences showed me that breaking down tough topics into simpler, real-life examples can make science less intimidating and more exciting for others. It\\u2019s rewarding to see friends go from frustration to curiosity!\",\"second-essay\":\"@Team 123 Hey everyone! \\ud83d\\udc4b I noticed the research idea proposal hasn\\u2019t been submitted yet. Deadlines are super important to keep the project on track, so let\\u2019s push through and finish this ASAP!  \\r\\n\\r\\nIf you\\u2019re stuck, let me know\\u2014I can help brainstorm or review drafts. Maybe we can set a new mini-deadline (like **48 hours**) to wrap things up? Even small progress counts!  \\r\\n\\r\\nRemember, this research could lead to something really cool, and I know you guys can do it. Let\\u2019s get it done together! \\ud83d\\udcaa  \\r\\n\\r\\n**Quick action steps:**  \\r\\n1\\ufe0f\\u20e3 Share what\\u2019s left to do.  \\r\\n2\\ufe0f\\u20e3 Ask for help if needed.  \\r\\n3\\ufe0f\\u20e3 Aim to submit in the next 2 days!  \\r\\n\\r\\nYou\\u2019ve got this! \\ud83d\\ude80  \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2014Fares\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 18:59:13'),
('SYSJ0286', '{\"full-name\":\"Fatma Ali \",\"email-address\":\"za9359067@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01153608002\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-06-04\",\"institution\":\"Bani sweif STEM School \",\"grade-year\":\"Grade 11\",\"gpa\":\"B\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy,Chemistry,Education,Mathematics,Medicine & Public Health,Neuroscience & Neurobiology,Psychology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"5\",\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"5\",\"Chemistry\":\"5\",\"Education\":\"5\",\"Mathematics\":\"5\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"5\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\",\"Psychology\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 15:30:57'),
('SYSJ0287', '{\"full-name\":\"Rawda Elmaghraby\",\"email-address\":\"rawdaalmaghraby@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01024721023\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-06-18\",\"institution\":\"Red Sea STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"G11\",\"gpa\":\"3.6\",\"interest\":[\"Aerospace Engineering,Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy,Physics & Astrophysics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Aerospace Engineering\":\"5\",\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"5\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"Firstly, my academic goals are to develop my knowledge of physics, or in other words, to learn more about it and also in the field of astronomy. On the other hand, my guiding goals lie in the fact that I like to benefit people with the information I have, so I have no objection to providing them with it when I acquire it.\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 10:29:48'),
