('SYSJ0313', '{\"full-name\":\"Aliya Zharkynova\",\"email-address\":\"zharkynovaaliya@mail.ru\",\"contact-number\":\"+7 708 223 78 05\",\"country\":\"Kazakhstan\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-04-04\",\"institution\":\"Nazarbayev Intellectual School of Physics and Mathematics of Taraz city\",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"5.0\",\"interest\":[\"Business\",\" Entrepreneurship\",\" & Strategy\",\"Economics\",\"International Relations & Government\"],\"grade-previous\":\"N\\/A\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"9\",\"Economics\":\"7\",\"International Relations & Government\":\"6\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 19:21:30'),
('SYSJ0315', '{\"full-name\":\"Youseff Samir Mohammed Gaber \",\"email-address\":\"yousef.3024063@stembewcairo.edu.moe.eg\",\"contact-number\":\"01061832010\",\"country\":\"Egyptian \",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-11-03\",\"institution\":\"New Cairo STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"G11\",\"gpa\":\"3.8\",\"interest\":[\"Chemistry,Computer Science,Data Science,Education,Mathematics,Robotics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Chemistry\":\"7\",\"Computer Science\":\"9\",\"Data Science\":\"8\",\"Education\":\"10\",\"Mathematics\":\"7\",\"Robotics\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"As a STEM student I have helped my colleagues who canot understand the STEM curriculum , I have designed books for children who in the primary stage , etc\",\"second-essay\":\"Hi , Good Morning \\r\\nPlease team 123 as a great team I know that you have collaborated with each others to make a great work but unfortunately you have skipped the deadline and it is very important to submit the project today. \\r\\nWith my best wishes,  youseff\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 20:43:42'),
('SYSJ0316', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-08-08\",\"institution\":\"STEM oct 11 th district\",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"3.7\\/4\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"100 percentage.\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in scientific research extends beyond simply transferring knowledge it requires a deep understanding of scientific principles and, more importantly, the emotional intelligence to guide students through intellectual and personal challenges. This quote resonates with me because I have experienced both sides: as a mentee inspired by passionate mentors and as a mentor who strives to ignite curiosity and resilience in others. My scientific journey has equipped me with the technical knowledge and the patience necessary for impactful mentorship. Through my work in biology, medicine, public health, neurobiology and neuroscience. I have developed skills in experimental design, data analysis, and critical thinking. However, I\\u2019ve come to realize that research is rarely a straight path it\\u2019s often filled with setbacks and complex puzzles. One of my proudest mentoring experiences involved guiding a group of younger students working on a science competition related to biology. they struggled with understanding the underlying physics of their prototype and were on the verge of giving up. I didn\\u2019t simply offer them the answers. Instead, I walked them through the problem, step by step, encouraging them to ask the right questions and explore different approaches. Over time, they grew confident not only in their solution but in their ability to tackle future challenges independently. This moment solidified my passion for mentorship helping students not just succeed in a project but develop the mindset of a scientist.\",\"second-essay\":\"The first, I know the problem to help them to send the task. I encourage them to work hard to send the task. I follow them step by step to finish the task. if they do not have problem, I will give them awareness.\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 21:51:32'),
('SYSJ0317', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 21:23:30'),
('SYSJ0319', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-03 22:35:34'),
('SYSJ0320', '{\"full-name\":\"Housam Tareq\",\"email-address\":\"housamtareqobaid10@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01002532359\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-02-13\",\"institution\":\"there isnt\",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Medicine & Public Health,Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"8\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"9\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"biology : 19 from 20   \",\"first-essay\":\"I believe mentorship in science is not just about knowing informations, but about sharing your passion and helping others when they feel stuck. In my journey, I always loved biology and tried to understand how science works not only in books but also in real life. Even I didnt do big scientific research yet because Im still in high school, I always try to read medical articles and learn how researchers think and write.\\r\\n\\r\\nMy goal is to one day lead medical research and also help other students like me who come from small places with low chances. I know many young students feel lost or not good enough, but with the right support they can do amazing things. I always try to explain science to my friends in simple way, like when we studied about DNA and some of them didn\\u2019t understand, I drawed them a small diagram and explained step by step and then they got excited.\\r\\nYSJ is a place I really admire because it gives real research exposure and teaches leadership. I believe if I join, I can improve my skills and also help other students who are new to research and science. I\\u2019m still learning, but I\\u2019m ready to work hard and support others too\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"second-essay\":\"Hello Team 123,\\r\\n\\r\\nI hope youre all doing well. I just wanted to gently remind you that the deadline for submitting the Research Idea Proposal has passed. I understand that things can get overwhelming sometimes, and that\\u2019s completely okay \\u2014 we all face moments like that.\\r\\n\\r\\nHowever, as part of YSJ, we\\u2019re expected to stay committed and responsible toward our tasks. I believe in your potential and I\\u2019m confident that you can still submit something meaningful if you focus now.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease try to complete and send your proposal as soon as possible. If there\\u2019s anything blocking your progress \\u2014 confusion, questions, or need for feedback \\u2014 don\\u2019t hesitate to reach out. Im here to help, not just as a senior, but as part of your team.\\r\\n\\r\\nLet\\u2019s finish strong.\\r\\n\\r\\nBest,\\r\\nHousam\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 22:19:31'),
