('SYSJ0344', '{\"full-name\":\"Jishantu Kripal\",\"email-address\":\"jishantukripal9@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+919954924045\",\"country\":\"India\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2002-02-07\",\"institution\":\"Jorhat Institute of Science and Technology\",\"grade-year\":\"2024\",\"gpa\":\"8.85\",\"interest\":[\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy,Computer Science\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"9\",\"Computer Science\":\"6\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Computer Science - 8\\/10\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-02 18:32:32'),
('SYSJ0345', '{\"full-name\":\"Salma abd elghany \",\"email-address\":\"salmaabdelghany452@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01055402010\",\"country\":\"Menoufia \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-05-18\",\"institution\":\"STEM high school \",\"grade-year\":\"B+\",\"gpa\":\"3.7\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"No\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-04 01:46:39'),
('SYSJ0346', '{\"full-name\":\"Youssef Adel \",\"email-address\":\"youssefadelkhattab2006@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201033465110\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2006-01-01\",\"institution\":\"Ain shams university - Faculty of veterinary medicine \",\"grade-year\":\"first year in uni\",\"gpa\":\"2.5\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"9th grade: 4.0, 10th: 3.5, 11th: 3.5, 12th: 3.5.\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-02 21:49:41'),
('SYSJ0347', '{\"full-name\":\"Hazem Taha\",\"email-address\":\"hazemmtaha00@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201270313227\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-04-02\",\"institution\":\"Armand Hammer United World College of the American West (UWC-USA)\",\"grade-year\":\"Grade 11\",\"gpa\":\"4.00 (Unweighted)\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Gender Studies & Inequality,Sociology & Anthropology\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"10\",\"Gender Studies & Inequality\":\"7\",\"Sociology & Anthropology\":\"5\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Biology: A\",\"first-essay\":\"As a person deeply involved in research, both social and scientific, the quote reflects on how I can turn the difficulties I encountered in research into the goals of my mentorship.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe first goal is to build an initial and strong background of the field and its supporting research tools. For instance, many students may not have the knowledge that they can propose an experiment and write expected results instead of just doing review articles, and others mistakenly think that a review article is just a display of current and previous research, not a way to draw further conclusions and encourage future research. In social sciences and gender studies, they may not know the basics they need for empirical research, like how to prepare and extract manuscripts from an interview, how to manipulate quantitative data using SPSS, the same for qualitative data using NVIVO, and finally draw non-biased conclusions. Such knowledge will help them choose a more successful approach to their research inquiries.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe second goal is to give scholars\\/junior researchers their space to decide. The decision of which methodology, research questions, or even tools to use should be authentic and only based on what the junior researchers want. As my goal is to only supervise, I may not intervene in their research process.\\r\\n\\r\\nFinally, my third goal is to help them leverage every single source they can. In my previous research programs, some had mentoring faculty feedback, and others had writing centers. I\\u2019m not sure what resources YSJ has, but I will do my best to make my scholars make the most out of them.\",\"second-essay\":\"Good evening\\/morning to you all,\\r\\n\\r\\nI noticed that your team did not submit the research proposal. Can you inform me of any obstacles you are currently facing or hardships? Finally, please submit as soon as possible and stick to the upcoming tasks for a better evaluation, which I have been expecting for such wonderful junior researchers like you!\\r\\n\\r\\nBest,\\r\\nHazem\\r\\n\",\"third-essay\":\"I have been involved in research in various fields and research programs.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn biology, I have had 3 research experiences, starting with a minimal school task on nutrition in STEM schools. My team and I were able to assess the nutritional qualities and energy in the daily servings versus an average basal metabolic rate  (BMR) and what an average high school student needs (attached). Then, I joined YSJ and conducted research (with Ali, B.) on how ADHD symptom severity could be related to malnutrition and\\/or school days (attached in the next page). I then joined Pioneer Academics with mentoring faculty Dr. David Veselik. I am currently preparing an experiment proposal on using allogeneic chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) T cells by a CRISPR Cas-CLOVER system to kill HIV-infected cells after reversing latency. I have finished a first draft of the introduction and literature review (https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/1_o-BeYvcCnIdNoOEO21bTj1jGmIsNFa8\\/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=110838578479928036253&rtpof=true&sd=true).\\r\\n\\r\\nIn gender and social studies, I had two research experiences. It started with Lumiere Education Individual Research Program with mentoring faculty Dr. Jaleah Rutledge and Dr. Teju Limbu. I finished a literature review paper on how menstruation is typically gendered, the hardships cis women and trans men face in the workplace because of menstruation,  perspective of trans women on menstruation, and recommendations (https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/file\\/d\\/1hfwp0mN_2eDfWdvXG9pFn0R7VNNWNjc3\\/view?usp=sharing). I then joined Daftar Ahwal Data research and management program, and built a quantitative archive on the incidents of violence in Egyptian schools and correlated it with gendered patterns in the report (https:\\/\\/drive.google.com\\/drive\\/folders\\/1MitW1ZqY1CzvFA5pwJIX9xKKkMSUt7dj?usp=sharing). \\r\\n\\r\\n** Note: the portal is only accepting one file. Thus, the mistakes of A Comparative Study of the Perceived Stress Levels and Sources of Stress are highlighted in the following document: https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/document\\/d\\/11mzvn6QT8YAtVVPIoB4IpjqbwdRQQxXg\\/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=110838578479928036253&rtpof=true&sd=true **\",\"hours_commitment\":\"10\",\"time_blocks\":\"Nothing significant\",\"hear_about\":\"I was a junior researcher\"}', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"A4 poster.Nutrition Investigators.10E.pdf\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0347\\/drafts\\/A4_poster.Nutrition_Investigators.10E.pdf\",\"size\":247299,\"type\":\"application\\/pdf\"}],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[{\"name\":\"Final Paper IFYR.docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0347\\/drafts\\/Final_Paper_IFYR.docx\",\"size\":683493,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"}]}', '2025-07-03 00:34:59'),
('SYSJ0351', '{\"full-name\":\"Diana Ebrahim Esmael Arafat\",\"email-address\":\"471906397@redsea1.moe.edu.eg\",\"contact-number\":\"01221681451\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2010-11-27\",\"institution\":\"Mohamed Eltayeb E.D.L School \",\"grade-year\":\"Grade 8\",\"gpa\":\"4.0\",\"interest\":[\"Aerospace Engineering,Arts,Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy,Computer Science,Education,Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering),Environmental Science,History & Civilizations,International Relations & Government,Linguistics,Mathematics\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Aerospace Engineering\":\"5\",\"Arts\":\"10\",\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"8\",\"Computer Science\":\"10\",\"Education\":\"7\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"5\",\"Environmental Science\":\"5\",\"History & Civilizations\":\"6\",\"International Relations & Government\":\"5\",\"Linguistics\":\"6\",\"Mathematics\":\"10\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Computer Science 99%\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-03 02:29:17');
