('SYSJ0372', '{\"full-name\":\"Youssef Tarek Mohammed Abd EL Azem Mohammed\",\"email-address\":\"yt77647@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01060199608\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-11-04\",\"institution\":\"STEM High for Boys - 6th of October\",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"4.0\",\"interest\":[\"Computer Science,Data Science\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Computer Science\":\"5\",\"Data Science\":\"7\"},\"grade-previous\":\"B+\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-03 22:34:19'),
('SYSJ0373', '{\"full-name\":\"Ganna Soliman\",\"email-address\":\"gannasoliman52@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01272924132\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2005-02-06\",\"institution\":\"Ain Shams University\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-03 23:28:35'),
('SYSJ0374', '{\"full-name\":\"Shaimaa Mohammed\",\"email-address\":\"etmanshimaa910@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01062567349\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-02-18\",\"institution\":\"Kafr Elsheikh STEM School \",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"3.83\\/4\",\"interest\":[\"Biology,Computer Science,Mathematics,Medicine & Public Health\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"9\",\"Computer Science\":\"8\",\"Mathematics\":\"7\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"10\"},\"grade-previous\":\"A+\\/A\\/B+\\/A+\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-03 23:34:57'),
('SYSJ0375', '{\"full-name\":\"\",\"email-address\":\"\",\"contact-number\":\"\",\"country\":\"\",\"birth-date\":\"\",\"institution\":\"\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-04 00:28:39'),
('SYSJ0376', '{\"full-name\":\"Mariam Amir \",\"email-address\":\"mariamamirhanna4@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01204719255\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-04-26\",\"institution\":\"The Model School \",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"93% \\u2248 4\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"4\",\"first-essay\":\"Some students fear data. Others fear the unknown. As a young researcher and mentor, I\\u2019ve learned to meet both with curiosity\\u2014and help others do the same.\\r\\nMy journey in scientific research began with questions: How can waste become a solution? Can technology decode environmental damage? These questions led me to research carbon-silica nanocomposites for bone scaffolds, develop AI models to predict microplastic pollution, and  platforms to promote recycling and rainwater harvesting. But the turning point wasnt publishing or awards\\u2014it was when I saw my first student\\u2019s eyes light up after finally grasping how brain synapses transmit signals. That moment redefined research for me: from isolated discovery to shared transformation.\\r\\nI believe mentorship is an act of translation\\u2014turning complexity into clarity and fear into fascination. As a science tutor, I guided students through confusing concepts in neuroscience, biology, and environmental systems. Using visual storytelling, analogies from daily life, and gamified feedback, I helped students who once dreaded science become eager explorers. One of them later messaged me: I want to be a climate scientist like you. That, to me, is success.\\r\\nYSJ\\u2019s mission to uphold rigorous standards while empowering young minds speaks directly to my dual passion: research and mentorship. I\\u2019m excited to contribute to a community where I can help others ask bold questions, embrace messy data, and celebrate small insights. I see myself not just leading in research, but building bridges\\u2014between confusion and understanding, between fear and excitement.\\r\\nIn every mentee, there is a future scientist. I hope to be the voice that tells them, \\u201cYes, you belong here.\\u201d\",\"second-essay\":\"If I were a YSJ Senior Researcher and Team 123 missed the proposal deadline, I wouldn\\u2019t just remind them\\u2014I\\u2019d re-ignite their purpose. Here\\u2019s how I\\u2019d approach it:\\r\\n\\r\\n\\ud83e\\udde0\\ud83d\\udcac Message to Team 123 via Discord:\\r\\nHey Team 123 \\ud83c\\udf31,\\r\\nYour silence is louder than you think\\u2014and it\\u2019s not like you.\\r\\nDeadlines at YSJ aren\\u2019t just dates they\\u2019re launchpads. You\\u2019re standing at the edge of an idea that could change how we see the world\\u2014and I won\\u2019t let it go to waste.\\r\\nMissing this proposal means missing the opportunity to take your first real step as researchers. So, here\\u2019s what we\\u2019ll do:\\r\\n1. You have 24 hours to regroup and submit your research idea.\\r\\n2. If youre stuck,  me a DM\\u2014I\\u2019ll walk you through. No judgment. Just progress.\\r\\n3. Remember: research doesn\\u2019t have to be perfect. But it has to begin.\\r\\nI believe in your minds. Now show me your momentum.\\r\\n\\u2014 Mariam,\\r\\nSenior Researcher  Biology & Environmental Science \\ud83d\\udca1\\ud83c\\udf0d\",\"third-essay\":\"From the bustling labs of Egypt\\u2019s National Research Centre to late-night Zoom calls with researchers across time zones, my research journey has been anything but ordinary. I\\u2019ve always been drawn to the intersection where science meets purpose\\u2014where ideas are not just explored but applied to improve lives.\\r\\n\\r\\nCurrently, I\\u2019m honored to be working with Dr. Sakthi at Brown University through the Talaria Summer Institute, diving into climate-focused research that explores technologys role in building a more sustainable future. This builds on my earlier work, from crafting an AI-powered honeypot to combat cyber threats under the guidance of a Stanford-affiliated mentor, to developing carbon-silica nanocomposites for bone scaffolds at a biotechnology lab.\\r\\n\\r\\nBut for me, research goes beyond the lab. It\\u2019s a way to answer urgent questions\\u2014How can AI help us protect marine ecosystems? What if a website could inspire communities to turn kitchen waste into energy? These questions shaped my projects: from an AI bot predicting microplastic hotspots, to a smart recycling platform with gamified tools for public engagement.\\r\\n\\r\\nI\\u2019ve also written extensively\\u2014publishing environmental articles, five educational books, and a climate adaptation study that earned me a top spot out of 37,500 global participants in the Climate Science Olympiad.\\r\\n\\r\\nBeyond titles and metrics, what drives me is impact. Whether tutoring younger students, co-founding an opportunity-sharing platform for youth, or volunteering at hospitals and environmental campaigns, I see science as a tool for empowerment. My work is grounded in a simple belief: research should reach beyond papers\\u2014it should plant trees, solve real problems, and inspire others to act.\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\",\"application_id\":77}', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"climate Science Olympiad (2).docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0376\\/drafts\\/686987dfc04bf_climate_Science_Olympiad__2_.docx\",\"size\":34916,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"},{\"name\":\"IYRC Abstract.docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0376\\/drafts\\/686988459645a_IYRC_Abstract.docx\",\"size\":1506927,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"}],\"commented_files\":[{\"name\":\"Document (41.docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0376\\/drafts\\/686990e689dd2_Document__41.docx\",\"size\":16089,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"}],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 21:02:31'),
