('SYSJ0401', '{\"full-name\":\"Eyad Ashraf\",\"email-address\":\"eyad@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01111605702\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"birth-date\":\"2025-07-16\",\"institution\":\"STEM\",\"grade-year\":\"Grade Year\",\"gpa\":\"A\",\"interest\":[\"Aerospace Engineering\",\"Architecture\",\"Arts\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Aerospace Engineering\":\"1\",\"Architecture\":\"7\",\"Arts\":\"3\"},\"grade-previous\":\"Grade of each respective field in previous academic years (if applicable)\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\\r\\n\\r\\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science\\r\\nMentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\\r\\n\\r\\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science\\r\\nMentorship in scientific research requires a comprehensive understanding of the concepts and the ability to motivate and direct students as they go through their difficulties. Analyze this quote and discuss how your experiences and knowledge in scientific research have prepared you enough to fit yourself into YSJs high standards.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn your response, state your academic and mentoring goals, explaining how some aspects of YSJ would help you direct young researchers toward their potential.\\r\\n\\r\\nFurthermore, give examples of situations where you have helped learners wade through complex problems to aid their growth and excitement for science\",\"second-essay\":\"Consider youre a YSJ senior researcher. One of your teams, perhaps team 123, has failed to stick to the Research idea proposal deadline. Write a message youd send them via discord to push them to finish their task\",\"third-essay\":\"Please describe your research background, including your areas of expertise, the research projects (e.g., papers, projects, and\\/or patents) you have been involved in, and\\/or any publications or presentations resulting from your research. (Word Limit: 150-300 words)\\r\\nPlease describe your research background, including your areas of expertise, the research projects (e.g., papers, projects, and\\/or patents) you have been involved in, and\\/or any publications or presentations resulting from your research. (Word Limit: 150-300 words\\r\\nPlease describe your research background, including your areas of expertise, the research projects (e.g., papers, projects, and\\/or patents) you have been involved in, and\\/or any publications or presentations resulting from your research. (Word Limit: 150-300 words\\r\\nPlease describe your research background, including your areas of expertise, the research projects (e.g., papers, projects, and\\/or patents) you have been involved in, and\\/or any publications or presentations resulting from your research. (Word Limit: 150-300 words\\r\\nPlease describe your research background, including your areas of expertise, the research projects (e.g., papers, projects, and\\/or patents) you have been involved in, and\\/or any publications or presentations resulting from your research. (Word Limit: 150-300 words\",\"hours_commitment\":\"5\",\"time_blocks\":\"List down the most significant time blocks you have between the start of June and the end of September.\",\"hear_about\":\"Where did you hear about YSJ?\",\"edit_mode\":\"1\",\"application_id\":67}', '{\"research_files\":[{\"name\":\"screen.png\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0401\\/final\\/screen.png\",\"size\":158619,\"type\":\"image\\/png\"}],\"commented_files\":[{\"name\":\"EBO Website.docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0401\\/final\\/EBO_Website.docx\",\"size\":22184,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"}],\"additional_files\":[{\"name\":\"screen.png\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ0401\\/drafts\\/686965b8ae92c_screen.png\",\"size\":158619,\"type\":\"image\\/png\"}]}', '2025-07-05 17:49:44'),
('SYSJ0402', '{\"full-name\":\"Hana Ehab\",\"email-address\":\"hanaehab815@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201009216663\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-12-01\",\"institution\":\"El future school\",\"grade-year\":\"10\",\"gpa\":\"3.4\",\"interest\":[\"Aerospace Engineering\",\"Biology\",\"Business\",\" Entrepreneurship\",\" & Strategy\",\"Computer Science\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\",\"Environmental Science\",\"Mathematics\",\"Medicine & Public Health\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\",\"Robotics\"],\"grade-previous\":\"Not applicable \",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Aerospace Engineering\":\"5\",\"Biology\":\"5\",\"Business, Entrepreneurship, & Strategy\":\"5\",\"Computer Science\":\"5\",\"Engineering (not Aerospace Engineering)\":\"5\",\"Environmental Science\":\"5\",\"Mathematics\":\"5\",\"Medicine & Public Health\":\"5\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\",\"Physics & Astrophysics\":\"5\",\"Robotics\":\"5\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 20:18:40'),
('SYSJ0404', '{\"full-name\":\"Abdelrahman Ahmed Ibrahim Azzam\",\"email-address\":\"abdelrahman.azzam111yahoo@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01030672841\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-05-02\",\"institution\":\".\",\"grade-year\":\"\",\"gpa\":\"\",\"interest\":[\"Mathematics\",\"Psychology\",\"Public Policy\",\"Robotics\"],\"grade-previous\":\".\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Mathematics\":\"7\",\"Psychology\":\"8\",\"Public Policy\":\"9\",\"Robotics\":\"8\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 18:26:08'),
('SYSJ0406', '{\"full-name\":\"Shrouk Alameldin\",\"email-address\":\"shroukalameldin990@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01098286093\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2008-11-02\",\"institution\":\"Gharbiya STEM School\",\"grade-year\":\"Grade 11\",\"gpa\":\"3.84\",\"interest\":[\"Biology\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"In my opinion, mentoring in scientific research goes beyond sharing knowledge it requires a commitment to the science as well as the understanding of motivating and guiding students as they navigate obstacles. Over my academic and research career, I have gained considerable expertise within my field and this has made me an effective mentor who helps others to appreciate science at a much deeper level.\\r\\n\\r\\nAs a researcher, I aim to evolve within my profession, while also striving to share impactful contributions to my area of expertise. In addition, I possess a strong sense of commitment towards mentorship by guiding students and early-stage researchers stimulate their intellectual curiosity while retracting difficulties, both conceptually and methodologically. It is my aim to help learners close the gap between vague understanding and meaningful comprehension \\u2013 I aspire to help construct pathways from confusion to mastery.\\r\\n\\r\\nWith their high academic standards and emphasis on student-centered supervision, York St John University (YSJ) offers the perfect environment to achieve these goals. The emphasis on interactive as well as tailored teaching and holistic learning sets YSJ apart from other institutions. This philosophy aligns seamlessly with my vision of mentorship, which, in my opinion, goes beyond teaching mentorship entails walking with the learner in their discovery journey.\\r\\nAs I reflect on my professional practice, I realize I have been able to support learners in solving multifaceted problems. For example, I remember assisting a student from molecular biology with a research project. They found a particular theoretical model quite challenging. Instead of providing the answer, I applied guided questioning for each part of the theory so that they could understand it better. Ultimately, they not only completed the project but also developed a passion for research afterwards.\\r\\nI personally value those instances when the student shifts their mindset and moves past a mental block to engage with challenging material \\u2014 for me, that is the essence of research mentorship. That is the learning experience that I wish to replicate over and over again. I appreciate the opportunity to join the YSJ community because I understand such pedagogical approaches are welcomed to nurture scientific enthusiasm.\",\"second-essay\":\"Dear Team 123,\\r\\n\\r\\nI notice that we have surpassed the proposal deadline and I haven\\u2019t received anything from your team. To be frank, this cannot slide at this stage. However, I do want to emphasize that I am here because I know what this team can deliver.\\r\\n\\r\\nI understand you\\u2019ve ped the ball here, but there is still time to pick it back up and take off with it.\\r\\n\\r\\nDeadlines in research have purposes such as creating momentum, offering structure, and providing a pathway toward progress. Just because a deadline is missed, it does not equate to failure. The best researchers are not perfect they are resilient. Each time they miss their mark, they come back stronger, sharper, and with ten much more.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is the action plan:\\r\\n\\r\\nYou have 48 hours to complete this goal. You must send me a fully thought out, clear, and intention-driven plan draft. Even if it is rough, just make sure to move.\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you feel stuck in any possible way, reach out today. There will not be any judgment met with your issue, only solutions. That is what teams do.\\r\\n\\r\\nRemind yourself every once and a while why you are here. You are not just filling a basic checkbox you are creating concepts that have the potential to change how we view the globe. That is powerful, far from small.\\r\\n\\r\\n\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Biology\":\"8\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 20:29:59'),
('SYSJ0407', '{\"full-name\":\"Noor Belal\",\"email-address\":\"noor2009noor2024@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01027726070\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2009-05-23\",\"institution\":\"Elsadat STEM High School\",\"grade-year\":\"11\",\"gpa\":\"3.78\",\"interest\":[\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\".\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\",\"gender\":\"male\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"5\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[]}', '2025-07-05 19:53:03'),
