('SYSJ085', '{\"full-name\":\"Sara ali \",\"email-address\":\"saraalihussienmahmoud@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"+201150777575\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-07-28\",\"institution\":\"\\u0645\\u062f\\u0631\\u0633\\u0629 \\u0666 \\u0627\\u0643\\u062a\\u0648\\u0628\\u0631 \\u0627\\u0644\\u0642\\u0648\\u0645\\u064a\\u0629 \\u0644\\u0644\\u063a\\u0627\\u062a\",\"grade-year\":\"11th grade\",\"gpa\":\"3.8\",\"interest\":[\"Environmental Science\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\",\"Psychology\"],\"grade-previous\":\"I dont study these subjects at school , i actually learned them from self learning, courses, competitions\",\"first-essay\":\"\",\"second-essay\":\"\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours\":\"\",\"time-blocks\":\"\",\"hear\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"4\",\"time_blocks\":\"All june -> travelling .   July -> i many sessions any these day so i am busy at theses day ->saturday, monday,wednesday\",\"hear_about\":\"From whats app student activities groups since 2024\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"interest_ratings\":{\"Environmental Science\":\"9\",\"Neuroscience & Neurobiology\":\"8\",\"Psychology\":\"10\"}}', '{\"research_files\":[],\"commented_files\":[],\"additional_files\":[{\"name\":\"ISEF 2024 abstract.docx\",\"path\":\"uploads\\/SYSJ085\\/drafts\\/686975d4a7cf5_ISEF_2024_abstract.docx\",\"size\":417973,\"type\":\"application\\/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document\"}]}', '2025-07-05 20:18:28'),
('SYSJ086', '{\"full-name\":\"Mary Emad\",\"email-address\":\"maryemad370@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01281210477\",\"country\":\"Egypt\",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"2007-04-22\",\"institution\":\"Maadi STEM School for Girls \",\"grade-year\":\"12\",\"gpa\":\"3.7\",\"interest\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"interest_ratings\":{\"Computer Science\":\"8\"},\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"ldmvkefnv \",\"second-essay\":\",mfdlemv.lv\",\"third-essay\":\"\",\"hours_commitment\":\"\",\"time_blocks\":\"\",\"hear_about\":\"\"}', '[]', '2025-07-01 17:05:46'),
('SYSJ087', '{\"full-name\":\"Ellen Youssef\",\"email-address\":\"ellen.youssef.ayad@gmail.com\",\"contact-number\":\"01212989642\",\"country\":\"Egypt \",\"gender\":\"female\",\"birth-date\":\"1998-12-01\",\"institution\":\"Zewail city for science and technology \",\"grade-year\":\"2021\",\"gpa\":\"3.5\",\"interest\":[\"\"],\"grade-previous\":\"\",\"first-essay\":\"Mentorship in scientific research requires not only deep subject knowledge but also the ability to inspire, guide, and support students through challenges. This philosophy has shaped my approach as a teaching and research assistant over the past two years, where I\\u2019ve combined technical instruction with encouragement to help students grow into confident, independent thinkers.\\r\\nWith a master\\u2019s degree in nanomedicine and a research focus on targeted drug delivery using polymeric nanoparticles, I\\u2019ve developed strong expertise in areas such as nanoparticle synthesis, DLS, zeta potential analysis, and advanced cell culture. My academic goal is to continue interdisciplinary research bridging nanotechnology and cosmetics, while my mentoring goal is to foster a learning environment that emphasizes curiosity, critical thinking, and resilience.\\r\\nYork St John University\\u2019s focus on research-led teaching and its commitment to nurturing student potential align perfectly with my values. I am particularly drawn to its emphasis on collaboration and its supportive academic community, which I believe provides the ideal setting for mentoring future scientists.\\r\\nOne of my most rewarding experiences involved helping a student struggling with nanoparticle data interpretation. Through weekly guidance and problem-solving sessions, she gained confidence and eventually presented her work in a student forum. Similarly, I supported a group conducting cytotoxicity assays by breaking down complex protocols, leading to a successful project and increased excitement about research.\\r\\nI am eager to contribute to YSJ\\u2019s academic excellence by combining my research skills and mentorship experience to guide young scientists toward realizing their full potential.\\r\\n\",\"second-essay\":\"Hi all, I hope you\\u2019re doing well.\\r\\nI noticed your Research Idea Proposal hasn\\u2019t been submitted yet, and the deadline has already passed. I understand things can get hectic, but timely submissions are critical\\u2014not just for planning, but also for showing commitment to your project.\\r\\nPlease prioritize wrapping this up and submitting it within the next 24 hours. If you\\u2019re facing specific challenges or need clarification, I\\u2019m here to help\\u2014don\\u2019t hesitate to reach out.\\r\\nLet\\u2019s stay on track and keep the momentum going. I\\u2019m looking forward to seeing what you\\u2019ve come up with.\",\"third-essay\":\"My research background centers on nanomedicine and targeted drug delivery, with a focus on the design and characterization of multifunctional nanoparticles for cancer therapy. I hold a master\\u2019s degree in nanomedicine, and my thesis focused on the formulation of polymeric nanocarriers encapsulating Doxorubicin and Metformin, aimed at hepatocellular carcinoma treatment. The formulation featured a PLGA core coated with PEI, surface-functionalized with folic acid and deoxycholic acid for enhanced targeting. This work integrates drug delivery, cancer biology, and surface modification, and the manuscript is currently under final revision for publication.\\r\\nIn parallel, I\\u2019ve worked for over two years as a teaching and research assistant at Zewail City of Science and Technology, where I supervised student research, conducted lab training, and contributed to projects involving nanoparticle synthesis, characterization techniques (DLS, FTIR, TEM), cytotoxicity assays, and advanced cell culture.\\r\\nAdditionally, I\\u2019m deeply interested in cosmetic science and am currently exploring the use of nanotechnology in hair and skin product formulation. I have also participated in academic conferences and internal university presentations where I presented aspects of my research.\\r\\nMy areas of expertise include nanoparticle design, surface functionalization, drug encapsulation, and biocompatibility evaluation. I\\u2019m highly skilled in laboratory techniques such as dynamic light scattering, zeta potential analysis, FTIR, and in vitro cytotoxicity studies. These experiences have honed my ability to conduct interdisciplinary research and contribute meaningfully to both academic and translational projects.\"}', '[]', '2025-06-18 21:08:24'),
